INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (2, 'Python Developer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-01 22:44:31', 'LISTED', 'Foxley Talent are currently searching for a fully remote Python Developer with experience in Django to join our client for a key role in their product team. This position will be working with a leading digital innovation company that provides tools to help online creators produce and share their latest content. The main platform is used to share content with billions of people worldwide. PLEASE BE AWARE, this company''s main product serves the adult entertainment industry. The successful Python Developer will have a background in web development and system design along with a track record of making technical decisions and taking ownership of their own work from start to finish. Having problem-solving skills and the ability to quickly troubleshoot and debug complex issues will be a key part of the role.. Experience Required:Worked with Django in a production environmentProfessional experience working with Python, Rust, and GoBackground working on sites with monthly users over 100, 000 (bonus points for 1 million plus)Exposure to cloud platforms like AWS or GCP Benefits:Base salary from $120, 000-$160, 000, based on experience.Ability to work fully remotely (within the United States ONLY)Full Health, Vision, Dental, and Life InsuranceUnlimited PTO and 12 Paid HolidaysOptional 401k with 5% matching The Annual Basic salary range for this position is $120, 000 - $160, 000. The successful candidate''s offered base salary will be determined based on their job-related skills and suitability for the position including any relevant education/training/experience etc. PLEASE BE AWARE, this company''s main product serves the adult entertainment industry. ONLY Applications from candidates based within the United States will be considered. There is no possibility for VISA Sponsorship or re-location.', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4066105736', 2, 2);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (3, 'Python Developer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-07 17:38:05', 'LISTED', 'Who We Are For more than 20 years, we have been working with organizations large and small to help solve business challenges through technology. We bring a unique combination of engineering and strategy to Make Data Work for organizations.  Our clients range from the travel and leisure industry to publishing, retail and banking. The common thread between our clients is their commitment to making data work as seen through their investment in those efforts.  In our quest to solve data challenges for our clients, we work with large enterprise, cloud based and marketing technology suites. We have a deep understanding of these solutions so we can help our clients make the most of their investment in an efficient way to have a data driven business.  Softcrylic now joins forces with Hexaware to Make Data Work in bigger ways!  Why Work at Softcrylic? Softcrylic provides an engaging, team-focused, and rewarding work environment where people are excited about the work they do and passionate about delivering creative solutions to our clients.  We are looking to add a Python Developer to our team! This is a Full-Time position and a Remote role.  Key Responsibilities:Bachelor''s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field.5+ years of experience in Python development with a focus on data engineering.Proficiency in SQL, including advanced queries, joins, indexing, and optimization.Experience with ETL tools and techniques (e.g., Airflow, Apache Spark, Talend).Strong understanding of relational databases (e.g., MySQL, PostgreSQL) and data warehousing concepts.Familiarity with data modeling and working with large datasets.Knowledge of cloud platforms (e.g., AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud) is a plus.Excellent problem-solving skills, attention to detail, and the ability to work independently.', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4071573638', 3, 1);
