INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (426, 'Software Developer (.NET)', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-11 21:18:54', 'LISTED', 'Who We Are.  Platinum Technologies is a Northern Virginia based integrated solutions firm that specializes in Cybersecurity, Cloud and Digital Services to the Public Sector. Our team solves hard problems and helps our Mission Partners achieve their goals. If you are self-motivated, possess demonstrated learning agility, and are passionate about delivering high-quality work products – we want to hear from you.  We lead with technical expertise, but that is just the tip of the iceberg – the ‘Why’ matters. At Platinum, we don’t hire people to do a job. We provide professional and leadership development to complement our self-motivated domain experts. Our teammates are dot-connecting leaders that operate in a mutually accountable environment to deliver thought leadership, expert technical analysis, and quality execution for our clients.  You.  Platinum Technologies is seeking a skilled Software Engineer specializing in Oracle server maintenance, WebLogic Server (WLS), and WebCenter Content (WCC). The ideal candidate will manage server patching, provide ongoing maintenance, and support critical web services. They will also handle security vulnerabilities, including ISVM and web scan findings, and implement automated notifications for any service outages.  What You Get To Do.  Perform Oracle server patching and maintenance for WebLogic Server (WLS) and WebCenter Content (WCC)Mediate and resolve ISVM and web scan security vulnerability findings, collaborating with Oracle as necessarySet up and maintain a high-availability environment for WebCenter ContentAutomate notifications for any critical website and service downtimesSupport applications at a 2nd-level, ensuring smooth operation and addressing issues as they ariseCustomize and enhance WCC features using specialized componentsSupporting applications as a primary or secondary support person   Required Skills.  Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related fieldMust be a U.S. CitizenExperience with customer-facingMinimum three – five (3-5) years experience in WebLogic Server (WLS) and WebCenter Content (WCC) 12c or laterAble to install Java, WLS, WCC patches with Oracle to mediate security vulnerability findingsCustomize WCC features using componentsProficient in installing Java, WLS, and WCC patches, and addressing security vulnerabilitiesStrong Understanding of the SDLC process and importance to various aspects involved in development of web applicationsFamiliarity with .NET development and experience working with WSDL/API calls is preferredMinimum two (2) + years experienced working with database systems, specifically Oracle DBMS, and experience integrating databases with .NET web applications   Preferred Skills:  Minimum two (2) + experience working with DB/RDBMS and using DB with .Net web applicationsExperience in .Net development, experience working with WSDL/API CallsAbility to work independently and in a team to maintain system uptime and implement improvementsExperience setting up high-availability environments and supporting enterprise-level applicationsStrong communication skills for technical and non-technical audiences   Platinum Technologies is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action employer. All qualified candidates will receive consideration for employment without regard to disability, protected veteran status, race, color, religious creed, national origin, citizenship, marital status, sex, sexual orientation/gender identity, age, or genetic information.', 'https://jobs.lever.co/pt78/8fe39d13-377d-4888-80a1-116aceb4964c/apply?lever-source=LinkedIn', 299, 1);
