INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (438, 'Software Engineer, Frontend ', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-12 17:17:31', 'LISTED', 'About Us:  Loloi Rugs is a leading textile brand that designs and crafts rugs, pillows, and throws for the thoughtfully layered home. Family-owned and led since 2004, Loloi is growing more quickly than ever. To date, we’ve expanded our diverse team to hundreds of employees, invested in multiple distribution facilities, introduced thousands of products, and earned the respect and business of retailers and designers worldwide. A testament to our products and our team, Loloi has earned the ARTS Award for “Best Rug Manufacturer” in 2010, 2011, 2015, 2016, 2018, and 2023. Security Advisory: Beware of Frauds Protect yourself from potential fraud and verify the authenticity of any job offer you receive from Loloi. Rest assured that we never request payment or demand any sensitive personal information, such as bank details or social security numbers, at any stage of the recruiting process. To ensure genuine communication, our recruiters will solely reach out to applicants using an @loloirugs.com email address. Your security is of paramount importance to us at Loloi, and we are committed to maintaining a safe and trustworthy hiring experience for all candidates.  SUMMARY: We are seeking a highly motivated and skilled Frontend Engineer to join our dynamic team. As a Frontend Engineer, you will play a pivotal role in working with our design & product teams to designing, developing, and maintaining our web applications from end to end. You will collaborate closely with our cross-functional teams to create innovative solutions that enhance user experiences and drive business growth. This position will report to our Director, Software Development.  Responsibilities Develop reliable, maintainable and scalable web applications on the cloud infrastructure Architect and implement UI components and reliable features based on functional and business requirements Maintain and expand the design system to ensure a consistent user experience across the application Collaborate with peer engineers, the product and design team in an agile environment to design and coordinate the development and testing of new features Participate in task breakdown and estimations, code reviews, bug fixes and deployment preparation Identify, test and propose improvements to the application for maintainability and scalability, and to accelerate functionality and performance Contribute to the SDLC process efficiency and effectiveness - optimize workflows, implement Best Practices, establish additional automation and tools integrations Maintain and optimize workstreams in accordance with established KPIs and proactively communicate any deviations and work with stakeholders to develop solutions and maintain project timelines and quality standards  Experience, Skills, & Ability Requirements 5-8 years of hands-on frontend software and UI/UX design development experience Strong experience developing web applications with React, and/or NextJS Strong proficiency in ES6, TSX, HTML5, and CSS3 Proficiency in using design tools such as Figma Knowledge of client-side, server-side rendering and SEO optimization Knowledge of A11Y best practices Experience in REST API and Webhook integrations Proficiency in responsive design Experience with TDD practices and testing tools such as Vitest, or Playwright Experience with version control systems like GitHub, GitLab or Bitbucket Experience creating solutions in an Agile environment. Experience working in a DevOps environment (we are on AWS & Vercel) Experience working in a CI/CD environment. Experience contributing and maintaining design systems  Nice to Have  Experience with cloud-based infrastructure and services like AWS, Azure or GPC; infrastructure as code Experience in eCommerce or FinTech startup/enterprise Experience working with globally distributed teams Competency in Microsoft Suite, Teams, JIRA, Confluence etc. Bachelor''s degree in Engineering, Computer Science, Information Systems, Business Administration, System Administration, or other related business, scientific or technical discipline  What We Offer Health, dental, and vision benefits Paid parental leave 401(k) with employer match A culture of meritocracy that fosters ongoing growth opportunities A stable, growing family-owned company that looks after its employees   Loloi Rugs does not discriminate on the basis of race, sex, color, religion, age, national origin, marital status, disability, veteran status, genetic information, sexual orientation, gender identity or any other reason prohibited by law in provision of employment opportunities and benefits. We seek a diverse pool of applicants and consider all qualified candidates regardless of race, ancestry, color, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, religion, national origin, citizenship, disability, Veteran status, marital status, or any other protected status. If you have a special need or disability that requires accommodation, please let us know.', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4072483967', 306, 1);
