INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (124, 'Full Stack Developer', false, '', '2024-11-01 20:23:55', 'LISTED', 'Job Title: Full-Stack Developer  Salary: $80, 000 - $130, 000 (based on experience)  Location: Alpharetta, GA - Hybrid (Mon, Tues, Thurs in-office; Wed, Fri remote)  Location Requirement: Candidates must already be current residents of Georgia and live within a 45-minute commute of Alpharetta. Applicants outside this area or those requiring relocation will not be considered.  Department: Development  Reports to: Vice President – Market Research & Insights  About The Role  As a Full-Stack Developer with our fintech client, you’ll play a vital role in creating and enhancing our web-based solutions for banks and credit unions. This position is focused on innovation, working to build three new solutions within our Adobe suite platform. You’ll work closely with both our front-end and back-end developers, creating a cohesive development environment to ensure seamless communication across teams.  Technical Stack  You’ll Work With a Cutting-edge Stack Including  Back-End: SQL, C#, .NET Framework Front-End: Angular, HTML, CSS, and TypeScript or JavaScript  Key Responsibilities Solution Development: Drive the creation of new systems and features in “Create” mode rather than maintenance. System Architecture & Design: Assist in crafting functional design specifications, project estimates, and system architecture. Collaboration: Work with a small team of developers, including junior members, guiding best practices and code reviews. Front-End Focus: Develop highly interactive, front-end applications, enhancing the user experience. Documentation & Testing: Document technical aspects, and support test cases/use cases for new and existing features. Stay Current: Keep up with new technologies and recommend integrations when beneficial, particularly in machine learning (ML) and other advanced tech.  Required Skills & Experience Technical Skills: .NET, Angular, SQL, JavaScript, H