INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (130, 'Cloud Application Developer (AWS)', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-08 12:00:56', 'LISTED', 'Cloud Application Developer (AWS) – CTP – Remote – $69.00 - $70.00/hr. The final salary or hourly wage, as applicable, paid to each candidate/applicant for this position is ultimately dependent on a variety of factors, including, but not limited to, the candidate’s/applicant’s qualifications, skills, and level of experience as well as the geographical location of the position. Applicants must be legally authorized to work in the United States. Sponsorship not available. Our client is seeking a Cloud Application Developer (AWS) for a remote opportunity. Role Description  Seeking an experienced Cloud Application Development Engineer with a strong understanding of the AWS cloud environment. The candidate should have a firm grasp on microservices architecture including an understanding of a Services Oriented Architecture (SOA), service isolation, horizontal scalability and other concepts included within the Twelve-Factor App methodology. The candidate will bring deep knowledge working with architectural patterns for cloud-native applications, including the use of cloud-based object storage, queues, load balancers, and containers in the cloud. The ideal candidate will have experience with AWS services such as Lambda, DynamoDB, and SQS, and container management services such as Glue and Lake Formation. As a developer, understanding DevOps practices, including value streams, feedback, and continuous improvement, will be needed. Job Responsibilities – What will the candidate be doing in the job? Day to Day? Team Size? Education Required?• Play a pivotal role in designing, implementing, and managing infrastructure as code, ensuring scalable, robust infrastructure and applications.• Implement CI/CD pipelines using SaaS services like GitHub, GitHub Actions, and AWS CodeDeploy.• Manage canary releases and blue-green deployments.• Manage the health and performance of cloud systems by implementing observability and responsive controls.• Ensure all data and infrastructure deployments comply with enterprise security and access controls, best practices, and standards.• Collaborate with partners and internal teams to design scalable and secure cloud architectures based on best practices and business requirements.• Develop and implement new business features and provide support for existing code.• Implement security measures and compliance. Skills & Requirements REQUIRED SKILLS• Bachelor''s degree in information technology or a related field.• 5+ years of experience designing and developing applications for an AWS cloud environment.• Proficiency in programming languages such as Python or Typescript. Having both is a bonus.NOTE: not interested in full stack Java developers; skills do not translate.• 5+ years of working with AWS services such as CloudWatch, CloudTrail, AWS S3, SQS, ELB, ECS, and Fargate.Ask if they have also used: S3, Lambda, Glue, AWS CDK "Huge Bonus", CloudFormation, and LakeFormationNOTE: one must have experience with serverless technologies and microservices. They are not interested in those with Ec2 experience (its not applicable)• 5+ years of experience with CI/CD pipelines with SaaS services such as GitHub, GitHub Actions, and AWS CodeDeploy.While in the future they plan to do containerization, they are not using this now, so candidates with Kubernetes and Docker are not relative.• 5+ years developing REST APIs with TypeScript and Python• 3+ years of experience integrating with third-party services with APIs.• 3+ years of experience working with infrastructure-as-code (IaC) using AWS CloudFormation with AWS CDK.• Expertise with Agile methodologies and experience working in Scrum teams with tools like Jira and Confluence• AWS Solution Architecture Professional, AWS DevOps Professional certification, or equivalent experience.• Excellent written and verbal skills• Creative problem solver with common sense and practical solutions orientation; must be passionate about technology and software development in improving business performance.• Must have experience developing custom scripts, procedures, and SQL queries• Should be well versed in test-driven development practices and tools with practical experience implementing linting / validation / testing pipelines (unit, integration, UAT).• Ability to make the appropriate recommendations based on the AWS Well-Architected framework and best practices for multiple AWS services.• Develop and deploy resilient and highly available cloud-based solutions to ensure uninterrupted services for critical applications.• Ability to work independently, set priorities, and mentor both internal and external teams PLUSES, NICE TO HAVES:• Familiarity with higher education (“EdTech”) systems, such as Student Information Systems, Learning Management Systems, and applicant portals.o Familiarity with EdTech technology standards such as LTI and SCORM Benefits/Other Compensation This position is a contract/temporary role where Hays offers you the opportunity to enroll in full medical benefits, dental benefits, vision benefits, 401K and Life Insurance ($20, 000 benefit). Why Hays? You will be working with a professional recruiter who has intimate knowledge of the industry and market trends. Your Hays recruiter will lead you through a thorough screening process in order to understand your skills, experience, needs, and drivers. You will also get support on resume writing, interview tips, and career planning, so when there’s a position you really want, you’re fully prepared to get it.  Nervous about an upcoming interview? Unsure how to write a new resume? Visit the Hays Career Advice section to learn top tips to help you stand out from the crowd when job hunting. Hays is committed to building a thriving culture of diversity that embraces people with different backgrounds, perspectives, and experiences. We believe that the more inclusive we are, the better we serve our candidates, clients, and employees. We are an equal employment opportunity employer, and we comply with all applicable laws prohibiting discrimination based on race, color, creed, sex (including pregnancy, sexual orientation, or gender identity), age, national origin or ancestry, physical or mental disability, veteran status, marital status, genetic information, HIV-positive status, as well as any other characteristic protected by federal, state, or local law. One of Hays’ guiding principles is ‘do the right thing’. We also believe that actions speak louder than words. In that regard, we train our staff on ensuring inclusivity throughout the entire recruitment process and counsel our clients on these principles. If you have any questions about Hays or any of our processes, please contact us. In accordance with applicable federal, state, and local law protecting qualified individuals with known disabilities, Hays will attempt to reasonably accommodate those individuals unless doing so would create an undue hardship on the company. Any qualified applicant or consultant with a disability who requires an accommodation in order to perform the essential functions of the job should call or text 813.336.5570. Drug testing may be required; please contact a recruiter for more information.', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4072110060', 92, 1);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (139, 'Python Developer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-12 15:38:52', 'LISTED', 'About Us  We are Digital Science and we are advancing the research ecosystem.  We are a pioneering technology company, and our vision is of a future where a trusted and collaborative research ecosystem drives progress for all. We believe in better, open, collaborative and inclusive research. In creating the next generation of tools and working in partnership with the community we tackle some of the biggest challenges to research. In order to achieve our vision, we need innovative, inspiring and dynamic people to join our team. Want to join us?  This role (due to Federal requirements) can only be satisfied by a “US citizen, US national, or US person” and additional checks may be required.  We also require this role to be based in the East Coast of the US, within EST/EDT time zone.   What you’ll be doing  Develop robust Python code for our ETL data pipeline, web applications, and APIsArchitect and administer cloud (AWS/Azure) infrastructure.Administer customer-specific Dimensions instances running on Kubernetes clusters.Plan, design and enhance automation processes, utilities and tools.Put into place release processes, infrastructure and tools.Help improve the reliability, scalability and performance of our systems.Work in a Federal and agile environment  What you’ll bring to the role  Core requirement:Strong hands on experience in a Python environmentAt least two items below are also required:Key Interest in DevOps and AWS/Azure cloud administration (architecting for scalability and high performance) with Kubernetes and DockerHigh familiarity with distributed systems and web technology, e.g., web services, message queuesProficiency in database systems and design with Oracle and PostgreSQL Experience with Solr, Elasticsearch and/or Lucene would be niceStrong experience with Linux administration and shell scriptingExperience with NginxUnderstanding of agile methodologiesMust be a self-learner, possessing inherent inquisitivenessExceptional problem solving and analytical skillsStrong interpersonal, communications, and organizational skills Living our Values  We invest in, nurture and support innovative businesses and technologies that make all parts of the research process more open, efficient and effective.  The Talent We Secure Is Fundamental To Us Achieving Our Vision And Our Growth Plans. The Values We Live By Are  We are brave in the pursuit of better  We are collaborative and inclusive  We are always open-minded  We are from and for the community  We''re an equal opportunity employer. All applicants will be considered for employment without attention to race, colour, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran or disability status  Additional Information  Please note that, in light of vaccination mandates for US Government contractors, Digital Science requires that all US-based employees are fully vaccinated against COVID-19, subject to approved accommodations.', 'https://holtzbrinck-careers.com/en/job/python-developer.html', 99, 1);
