INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (142, '100% Remote Senior Python Developer - Django', true, 'Remote', '2024-10-31 01:49:27', 'LISTED', 'Job Title: Remote Senior Python Developer  Location: 100% Remote  Salary: $120, 000 - $160, 000  Requirements: 5+ years with Python, Django, JavaScript, HTML, CSS, SQL, GIT  Position Overview  We are a mid-sized company that has been around for over 10 years in the a Real Estate Investment industry. Our company contains $6 billion in assets in over 45 states. Our clients always meet or exceed their investment goals. We work with corporations that are necessity based in retail and health industries.  We are seeking a highly skilled Remote Senior Python Developer to join our dynamic development team. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in Python and experience working with Django and unit tests. We are an exciting team of about 6 engineers. This role will bridge the gap between the Software Engineering Manager and the Junior Developers. We provide lots of growth opportunity and will evolve this role into a Lead position!  Candidates with completed questionnaires will be reviewed first!*  Key Responsibilities  Collaborate with cross-functional teams to design, develop, and implement complex software solutions using Python and DjangoWrite and maintain unit tests to ensure code quality and functionalityArchitect and design complex systems, considering factors such as scalability, performance, and securityUtilize HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to create clean and user-friendly interfacesWork with GIT to manage code versioning and mergesIntegrate RESTful APIs into software solutionsUtilize ticketing systems to track and prioritize tasksWork with Linux environments and utilize SQL for database management and queriesImplement and maintain CI/CD processes to ensure efficient and timely delivery of software  Qualifications  Bachelor''s degree in Computer Science or a related field (Plus)PythonDjango Unit Testing FrameworksArchitect and design complex systemsHTMLCSSJavaScriptGIT and version controlRESTful APIs IntegrationsTicketing systems (JIRA or Trello)LinuxSQL CI/CD   Benefits  100% Remote WorkMedical, Dental, and Vision Benefits - $490/month covered plus 50% coverage if there is a balance left over15 Days PTO within first year Profit Sharing after 1 year of employment  Email Your Resume In Word To  Looking forward to receiving your resume through our website and going over the position with you. Clicking apply is the best way to apply, but you may also:  wendy.warner@cybercoders.com  Please do NOT change the email subject line in any way. You must keep the JobID: linkedin : WW2-1813252L220 -- in the email subject line for your application to be considered.***  Wendy Warner - Lead Recruiter  For this position, you must be currently authorized to work in the United States without the need for sponsorship for a non-immigrant visa.  This job was first posted by CyberCoders on 07/31/2024 and applications will be accepted on an ongoing basis until the position is filled or closed.  CyberCoders is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer  All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, age, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, national origin, ancestry, citizenship, genetic information, registered domestic partner status, marital status, status as a crime victim, disability, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law. CyberCoders will consider qualified applicants with criminal histories in a manner consistent with the requirements of applicable state and local law, including but not limited to the Los Angeles County Fair Chance Ordinance, the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, and the California Fair Chance Act. CyberCoders is committed to working with and providing reasonable accommodation to individuals with physical and mental disabilities. If you need special assistance or an accommodation while seeking employment, please contact a member of our Human Resources team to make arrangements.  ', NULL, 101, 32);
