INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (177, 'Database Developer - Remote anywhere in the US', true, 'Remote', '2024-10-31 07:35:06', 'LISTED', 'What We Do  KinderSystems (www.KinderSystems.com) is the leading provider of subsidy management software-as-a-service (SaaS) solutions to state agencies, Head Start programs, and child care providers. Built and supported by industry experts, KinderSystems envisions a world where all families, no matter their income level, have access to high quality child care. Hundreds of agencies in the publicly funded child care sector use KinderSystems applications via the cloud or mobile devices to streamline their operations, ensure compliance with government regulations, and meet the needs of the families they serve.  \What You’ll Do With Us:   KinderSystems is looking for a talented Database Admin/Developer to round out the Applications and Interface teams. The role will be a critical part of a small team working with the client to design, implement, test, and deploy new import/export functionality, as well as triage and provide support for our existing enterprise solutions. The candidate will be intelligent, enthusiastic, creative, and a great communicator, with the knowledge and experience to develop and maintain complex backend code and ETL components.  Primary Responsibilities  Maintain and enhance new and existing backend application components and ETL processes including creation and modifying of stored procedures, SQL Job, SSIS packages, API''s, and PowerShell and Batch scripts. Analyze and troubleshoot complex data and performance issues, and provide technical solutions to help triage and resolve support related tickets. Job duties may shift focus between support related issues/tickets and more traditional project database development tasks, depending upon the client and project. Implement solutions clearly and concisely, resulting in code that is easy to understand and maintain. Debug and test all new and/or modified code. Creation of necessary technical documentation based on implementation details. Participate in daily product standups to report progress, work performed, and potential blocking issues or other problems. Participate in code reviews to ensure conformance to internal standards and specifications. Participate in product design sessions with clients to provide technical guidance as well as level of effort estimates for future planning. Work closely with the Quality Assurance team to provide technical support during testing phases. Stays current with technical training and company standards as required.   Who You Are  Minimum 2-4 years of recent experience with enterprise level Microsoft SQL Server and SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS) Strong Knowledge of Relational Database Design Strong Knowledge and understanding of ETL-related processing and best practices Strong Knowledge of T-SQL programming, including the development of stored procedures, functions, triggers, and views Ability to profile and performance tune stored procedures using query plan execution tools Comfortable working in an environment containing only small amounts of documentation, and experienced in tracking down issues and troubleshooting support tickets by following the “code trail”Team player capable of working in a small group as well as independently Strong interpersonal skills in communication, planning, organizing, analyzing, and problem-solving High attention to detail Experience working with Jira is a plus  What We Offer  The ability to work remotely from anywhere in the US Compensation range is $90-100, 000 annually; based on experience Benefits include medical, dental, vision, 401(k) with company match, and generous PTO Friendly, supportive, and adventurous environment with a team of engaged colleagues   KinderSystems actively embraces diversity and equal opportunity in a meaningful way. We are committed to building a team that represents a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and skills. The more inclusive we are, the better our work will be which is why we do not discriminate based on race, color, religion, marital status, age, national origin, ancestry, physical or mental disability, medical condition, pregnancy, genetic information, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, veteran status, or any other status protected under federal, state, or local law.  All persons hired will be required to verify identity and eligibility to work in the United States (without sponsorship) and complete the required employment eligibility verification form upon hire.', 'https://kindersystems.rippling-ats.com/job/826119/database-developer-remote-anywhere-in-the-us', 125, 1);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (145, 'Full Stack Developer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-11 17:55:44', 'LISTED', 'No H1  100% Remote Contract  Experience: 7+ years requiredInterviews: Guaranteed interviews for qualified candidates; two virtual interview roundsStart Date: Immediate, aiming to fill by next Friday  Job Summary  Care.com is looking for a seasoned Full Stack Developer to join their team, with a focus on backend Java development and front-end capabilities in React and TypeScript. The role also requires expertise in GraphQL to support dynamic data querying and efficient API management. The ideal candidate will work across the stack to build, integrate, and optimize web applications, ensuring a seamless experience for end users.  Key Responsibilities  Design, build, and maintain robust web applications using Java for backend and React with TypeScript for front-end.Implement GraphQL to streamline API queries, optimizing data fetching for performance.Ensure seamless data integration and management between front-end and back-end components.Collaborate with product and design teams to deliver innovative and user-centric solutions.Write clean, modular, and testable code, adhering to best practices in full-stack development.Conduct code reviews, troubleshoot issues, and ensure application security and performance.  Required Skills And Qualifications  7+ years of full-stack development experience with a focus on backend Java and front-end React and TypeScript.Proficient in GraphQL, with hands-on experience designing and implementing queries and schemas.Strong knowledge of Java and backend development practices.Skilled in creating responsive and dynamic front-end applications using React and TypeScript.Familiarity with CI/CD processes and deployment automation.Strong communication skills and ability to work efficiently in a remote setting.', 'https://candidateportal.ceipal.com/jobs/job_description/NkkvOGpKVjNNRkRQWkFXaVFsNlVsUT09#.job_boards.LinkedIn', 102, 1);
