INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (216, 'AWS DevOps Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-04 21:24:53', 'LISTED', 'NO C2C PLEASE!! We are seeking a candidate who is not only technically strong in CI/CD and cloud automation but also experienced in mentorship, cross-functional collaboration, and security compliance. They should be comfortable in an Agile environment, capable of solving complex problems with scripting and automation, and experienced with tools like Jenkins, AWS, Git, and Maven. This is a hands-on role that requires both technical expertise and the ability to coach and support application developers. EXPERIENCED IN:• Continuous Integration/Continuous Deployment (CI/CD):o Expertise in defining and documenting CI/CD best practices.o Hands-on experience with build/release tools like Jenkins, Maven, and similar tools for automating the build, test, and deployment pipeline.• Scripting and Automation:o Strong scripting skills in languages such as Python and Bash.o Automation experience using tools like Ansible for configuration management and deployment automation across multiple environments.o Ability to solve problems and automate workflows across multiple platforms through scripting.• Cloud Platforms:o Experience with AWS and cloud infrastructure, including knowledge of services like AWS CodeCommit for source control and AWS security policies.• Version Control Systems:o Proficiency in source control tools like Git, BitBucket, Subversion, or AWS CodeCommit to manage code repositories.• Artifact/Binary Management:o Familiarity with binary/artifact repositories such as Maven, Nexus, or Artifactory for managing code packages and dependencies.• Linux and OS-Level Experience:o Solid experience with the Linux operating system and bash scripting to perform administrative tasks and automation at the OS level.• Security Compliance:o Awareness and experience in implementing security policies in line with organizational security standards, ensuring systems comply with established security measures.• Agile/DevOps Mindset:o Experience working in Agile environments, using tools like Jira or VersionOne to manage tasks, sprints, and team collaborations.o Ability to work across multiple platforms and applications, understanding system dependencies and coordinating with business teams to align technical solutions with business needs.• Mentorship and Collaboration:o Ability to coach and mentor application developers in building scalable, efficient applications, and acting as a technical resource for product teams to improve speed-to-market and product quality. TECHNICAL PROFICIENCIES REQUIRED:• AWS• Python• APIs• Ansible• Jenkins, Maven• Linux OS• Bash scripting METHODOLOGIES/BEST PRACTICES:• CI/CD• Agile TOOLS:• Source Control Tools: Git, BitBucket, Subversion, or AWS CodeCommit• JIRA or VersionOne FAMILIAR WITH:• Binary/artifact repositories like Maven, Nexus, Artifactory, etc.', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4064857053', 154, 1);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (217, 'Senior Data Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-04 01:00:00', 'LISTED', 'Data IdeologyAt DI, we provide Data & Analytics expertise to drive measurable business outcomes, often solving complex business problems for our clients. Our data analytics advisory services enable our customers to transform data into insights by driving a culture of empowerment and ownership of results. Our team consists of highly motivated individuals passionate about learning, understanding, collaborating, and intellectually curious. For more information about Data Ideology, visit www.dataideology.com Senior Data Engineer - Full-timeWe are looking for a Sr. Data Engineer to join our growing team. Sr. Data Engineer will leverage their business and technical knowledge to develop production-ready data models by integrating multiple data sources while working with business and technical teams to understand business strategy and objectives, gather information, and ensure business requirements are being fulfilled throughout the entire data & analytics lifecycle.  ResponsibilitiesDesign, develop, and implement robust data models for enterprise systems and external sources, ensuring data is accessible, accurate, and consistently available for analysis.Act as a technical resource in executing data strategies and architectures, collaborating closely with data architects and stakeholders to ensure alignment.Advocate and adhere to software and data engineering best practices, leveraging cloud technologies to accelerate innovation.  Strategy & PlanningPartner with data architects, product teams, and business experts to create and execute a data management roadmap aligned with company objectives.Develop tactical solutions to meet immediate needs, while supporting long-term data architecture standards and vision.Collaborate across teams, including IT, Business Intelligence, Data Quality, and Data Governance, to ensure accurate data metadata and high standards of data quality.  Acquisition & DeploymentContribute to solution proposals with vendors and cloud providers, supporting the evaluation and selection of data solutions that meet company and client objectives.Plan and participate in initiatives for data security, backup, disaster recovery, and business continuity, aligning with best practices for data integrity and regulatory compliance.  Operational ManagementDrive best practices in data engineering workflows, from SDLC processes to source control and change management.Conduct peer reviews, mentoring team members to promote high standards and continuous improvement.Explore and implement tools and technologies to advance Data Ideology’s data engineering capabilities.Ensure efficient data mapping, movement, and integration across platforms, maintaining data quality and consistency.Support project managers and business leads on data-centric initiatives, facilitating successful data integration and system compatibility.  Additional ResponsibilitiesContribute to cloud cost optimization, data reuse, and tech-debt reduction, promoting sustainable data engineering practices.Regularly update and enhance the data architecture to keep up with evolving technologies and business needs.  Supervisory Responsibilities: NoneQualificationsEducation and Experience:Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, or a related field, or equivalent combination of education and experience.A minimum of seven (7+) years of relevant experience in data engineering or related fields.Solid understanding of data architecture concepts, data mining, and large-scale data modeling.Proficiency in cloud data technologies, with experience in platforms like Snowflake, Azure, or Google Cloud Platform (GCP).Familiarity with data governance principles, data quality standards, and security protocols.Strong programming skills in languages commonly used for data engineering (e.g., SQL, Python, Spark).Experience with DevOps practices, including source control, CI/CD pipelines, and deployment best practices. Work Environment: Remote work from home. Some travel to Pittsburgh, PA a few times a year.Hours of work and days are generally Monday through Friday. Specific business hours will depend on client needs. Physical Demands: Must be able to remain in a stationary position 50% of the time. The person in this position must occasionally move about inside the office to access file cabinets, library stacks, office machinery, etc. Constantly operates a computer and other office productivity machinery, such as a calculator, copy machine, and printer. The person in this position frequently communicates with clients and coworkers. Must be able to exchange accurate information in these situations. Benefits: Flexible Time Off PolicyInsurance (medical, dental, vision) for employees 100% company paid - short and long-term disability insurance for employees 100% company paid - life insurance and AD&D insurance for employees 100% company paid – employee assistance program Retirement plans with company match Training and Certification Reimbursement annually Performance-based incentive program Commission incentive program Profit Sharing Plan Referral Bonuses Data Ideology is an EEO Employer ', 'https://app.jazz.co/apply/job/vQG1TTfCc6?source=LINKR', 155, 37);
