INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (219, 'Full Stack Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-12 06:27:39', 'LISTED', 'About UsHireRoad is a leading global provider of HR solutions spanning recruitment, onboarding, learning, and analytics software. Driven by PeopleInsight, our best-in-class people analytics solution, we aim to power companies with better people data. Our mission is to help our customers maximize the impact of their HR technology through a deeper understanding and optimization of their most significant investment– their people. With nearly 400 customers across the United States, Australia, United Kingdom, and Canada markets, HireRoad empowers HR teams to maximize their impact through actionable data-driven insights, customized support from our team of experts, and a transparent, cost-effective approach to meet companies where they are at in their people data journey. About the RoleWe are looking for a skilled Full Stack Developer to join our team. The successful candidate will be responsible for developing and maintaining both the front end and back end of our web applications. You should have a deep understanding of web development technologies and a passion for creating user-friendly and efficient web interfaces. This role involves working closely with designers, product managers, and other developers to deliver high-quality software solutions. ResponsibilitiesDesign and implement front end interfaces for web applications using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and modern frameworks/libraries such as React, Angular, or Vue.js.Develop and maintain back-end services and APIs using technologies such as Node.js, and .NET.Collaborate with designers to translate UI/UX designs into functional and visually appealing web pages.Ensure the technical feasibility of UI/UX designs.Optimize applications for maximum speed and scalability.Integrate front end components with back-end services.Write clean, maintainable, and efficient code.Troubleshoot, debug, and upgrade existing applications.Conduct code reviews and provide constructive feedback to peers.Stay up to date with emerging technologies and industry trends. RequirementsBachelor''s degree in computer science, Engineering, or a related field.Proven experience (5+ years) as a Full Stack Developer or similar role.Strong proficiency in front end technologies: HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and frameworks/libraries such as React, Angular, or Vue.js.Proficiency in back-end technologies such as Node.js, and .NET.Experience with database management systems (e.g., MSSQL, PostgreSQL).Familiarity with version control systems (e.g., Git).Experience with AWS cloud platform.Knowledge of DevOps practices and tools (e.g., Docker, Kubernetes, CI/CD pipelines).Understanding of web security best practices.Understanding of RESTful API design and development.Knowledge of responsive design principles and mobile-first development.Knowledge of test-driven development, including unit testing and integration testing.Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.Excellent communication and teamwork skills.Ability to work independently and manage multiple projects simultaneously. What we offer you in returnPlay a key role in the expansion of a SaaS businessCollaboration with international offices on global projectsBacking from senior management to be disruptive – for positive outcome!Competitive salary/ratePotential to progress your role as we continue to expandContinuously and consciously working to ensure an empowering, team-oriented, and politically free environment And employee benefits such asMedical, Dental & Vision InsuranceStock Options401k plan with company matchGenerous holidays/Paid Time-offAdditional wellness day-off per month We at HireRoad, celebrate diversity and are dedicated to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. We are committed to equality of opportunity for all staff and applications from individuals are encouraged regardless of age, disability, sex, gender reassignment, sexual orientation, pregnancy and marital status, race or religion. We adhere to these principles in all aspects of employment, including recruitment, hiring, advancement, training, discipline, or discharge. HireRoad will not tolerate discrimination or harassment based on any of these characteristics. Regretfully, we do not provide visa sponsorship and to meet this job''s requirements, you must be legally entitled to undertake unrestricted, full-time work in the US.', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4066601162', 157, 64);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (220, 'Game Developer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-11 20:05:40', 'LISTED', 'Company Overview:We have a remote work-first organization, we respect each other, we value our lives outside of work, and we''re incredibly passionate about building something that will change the world for the better. Does this sound like a good fit? If so, then we would love to hear from you! Job Description:Avalon is seeking a talented and experienced Unreal Engineer to join our dynamic development team. In this remote role, you will design, implement, and optimize multiplayer features and systems using Unreal Engine. You will collaborate closely with designers, artists, and other engineers to deliver seamless and engaging online experiences for our global player base. An openness to Web3 technologies is highly valued as we explore integrating blockchain and decentralized systems into our games. Key Responsibilities:Development:Develop and implement core multiplayer gameplay mechanics and systems using Unreal Engine.Design networked features that ensure smooth and responsive gameplay across various platforms.Integrate Web3 technologies where applicable to enhance game functionality and player engagement.Optimization & Performance:Optimize network performance to handle high player counts with minimal latency.Troubleshoot and resolve networking issues, ensuring stability and scalability.Collaboration:Work closely with game designers to translate gameplay concepts into technical solutions.Collaborate with other engineers and departments to integrate multiplayer systems seamlessly.Testing & Quality Assurance:Implement automated testing for multiplayer features to ensure reliability.Participate in playtesting and iterate on features based on feedback and data analysis.Documentation & Best Practices:Maintain clear and comprehensive documentation of systems and processes.Advocate for and implement best practices in multiplayer game development. Qualifications:Education & Experience:Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field.OR equivalent practical experience.3+ years of experience in game development, with a focus on multiplayer systems.Technical Skills:Proficiency in C++ and Unreal Engine’s gameplay framework.Strong understanding of networking principles, client-server architecture, and synchronization techniques.Experience with Unreal’s networking libraries and replication system.Knowledge of client-side predictive systems and server authentication mechanisms.Familiarity with version control systems (e.g., Git, Perforce, Plastic).Soft Skills:Excellent problem-solving abilities and attention to detail.Strong communication and teamwork skills.Ability to work effectively in a remote, fast-paced, iterative development environment.Openness to learning and integrating Web3 technologies into game development. Preferred Qualifications:Experience with cross-platform multiplayer development.Knowledge of additional programming languages (e.g., Python, C#).Familiarity with server infrastructure and cloud services (e.g., AWS, Azure).Previous experience working on AAA titles or large-scale multiplayer projects.Experience with UI development and backend databases.Understanding of blockchain technology and decentralized systems.', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4074143025', 158, 1);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (224, 'C++ Developer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-07 20:29:45', 'LISTED', 'A boutique prop trading firm is seeking a C++ Software Engineer to develop innovative platforms and systems that support their trading and research efforts. The firm emphasizes building massively scalable, flexible, and future-ready platforms where performance is critical. Their collaborative environment fosters innovation and growth. As a C++ Software Engineer, you will work closely with traders, researchers, and other developers to design and implement cutting-edge, ultra-low latency, high-throughput trading systems. You will be involved in the entire lifecycle of projects, from conception to deployment, and play a key role in driving innovation for the frameworks supporting the firm''s trading applications. Additionally, you will benchmark and optimize critical software services to ensure peak performance. The firm employs a talented team of engineers recognized as leaders in their field. They are dedicated to hiring the best and brightest, providing them with the tools, autonomy, and support necessary for success. What we look for:Advanced proficiency in C/C++ systems development within a Linux environmentExpertise in performance tuning and optimizing low-latency softwareProven success in building high-performance software solutionsExperience developing latency-sensitive systems with a deep understanding of low-level systems and network developmentStrong knowledge of hardware stack and hardware architecture from a latency optimization perspectiveSolid understanding of network protocols1 - 7 years of experience We are flexible on experience and care most about caliber Role responsibilities C++ Development Tech stack C++, Python Employee benefits Engaging team activities such as ping pong and poker gamesRegular team outingsUnlimited office snacks and catered meals (breakfast, lunch, dinner)Free gym membershipComprehensive health insurance coverage for employees and dependents', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4071627303', 162, 1);
