INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (251, 'Full Stack Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-11 19:30:51', 'LISTED', 'Principal Full Stack Engineer Opportunity Join a Mission-Driven, Well-Funded Medtech and Life Sciences Startup Arm of a Public Company Are you an experienced full-stack engineer with expertise in gRPC, Go, and a drive to create transformative healthcare technology? If so, this might be worth reading on to at the the "what''s in it for you" section. GC holders and US citizens currently based in the US who have worked in a fullstack role for a health-tech/ telehealth/ biotech startup, please don''t be put off by the number of applications, as 95% of them won''t be relevant (or even be based in the US) and you''d really make my day to see your application, it won''t get lost in the noise and I will reach out to you. Role OverviewThis is a full-stack engineering role for a senior software engineer who can straddle both frontend and backend development, with a focus on cross-platform work. You’ll develop sophisticated healthcare applications using a tech stack that includes Flutter for the front end and Go for the backend, with support from Python and iOS native APIs. Familiarity with C++ is a major plus, as it will enhance your ability to work across systems and optimize performance. Your work will go beyond traditional full-stack development, requiring expertise in building secure, high-performance applications that meet the strict requirements of healthcare, including HIPAA compliance and integration with electronic medical records (EMR). While this isn’t a classic IoT role, it involves some IoT-like elements as you’ll work with computer vision models for medical imaging, processing real-world data from devices like cameras and medical imaging tools. This means handling high-efficiency data processing, image analysis, and potentially even device integration—skills often found in IoT, applied here to the healthcare setting. It’s full-stack development for a specialized, high-stakes environment where privacy, precision, and performance are critical. Why This Role? Mission-Driven Work: As the Principal Full Stack Engineer, you’ll lead the development of medical imaging and machine vision applications designed to advance wound care and patient outcomes. Your work will involve building secure, HIPAA-compliant applications that integrate seamlessly with electronic medical records and improve provider-patient interactions. Fully Remote Startup Environment: Join a team being built by Twelve10, the exclusive recruiter for this project. We’re building a core team for a healthcare and life sciences innovation venture, focused on delivering sophisticated mobile applications and backend solutions for healthcare. Industry-Agnostic Opportunities: If you’re a seasoned engineer fluent in multiple languages (Go, Flutter, Python) and proficient in designing scalable, high-availability systems, we want to hear from you—even if healthcare is a new industry for you. Support and Security: Work in a high-growth startup backed by the stability and resources of a leading public company in the medtech and life sciences sectors. You’ll have the agility of a startup with world-class healthcare and 401k/pension contributions typically found in established public companies. End-to-End Involvement: Lead software development across mobile and backend environments, ensuring compliance with FDA and global medical device standards. You’ll have direct impact on technical decisions, application architecture, and the integration of machine vision algorithms for wound care. What You’ll Bring to the Role:Technical Mastery: Your experience with full-stack development in Go, gRPC, Flutter, and relational databases (PostgreSQL preferred) will be essential for building robust applications across mobile and backend platforms.Cross-Platform Proficiency: If you have experience building applications across iOS, Android, MacOS, Windows, and Linux, you’ll appreciate the diverse technical landscape you’ll be working with.Leadership and Impact: This role offers you the chance to shape both strategic goals and tactical execution while fostering a collaborative, high-performing team culture.System Integration Expertise: Your knowledge of HIPAA-compliant EMR integration, cybersecurity, and scalable data management will ensure that patient data is handled securely and efficiently.Join us in building impactful technology at the intersection of healthcare, medtech, and life sciences. Twelve10 has been exclusively retained by a leading Private Equity investor to build this go-to-market team—apply now to be part of a mission that truly makes a difference.', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4074105406', 179, 72);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (252, 'Web Developer Intern', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-12 15:40:32', 'LISTED', 'Are you a web developer with a passion for creating innovative and user-friendly websites? Do you enjoy working as part of a collaborative team to improve design and usability? Ripple Effect is seeking a Web Developer Intern to join our dynamic team.Ripple Effect is looking for a graduate student to join our team as a Web Developer Intern to support our client''s mission. This role will be on the Digital Transformation team and will work with other teams to oversee the development of high-quality websites, collaborate with designers, and implement best practices to ensure optimal website performance and user experience.If this position sounds of interest, there''s a place for you here at Ripple Effect! We are a diverse, progressive, and engaging work environment. We offer a multitude of incentives and flexible work options that work for you and your lifestyle. General Information   Job Code: ADF-IN-00F  Location: Ripple Effect Headquarters - Rockville, MD   Employee Type: Non-Exempt, Part-Time, On-Call (Ask our recruiters about flexible work arrangements)  Telework: Part-Time, On-Call  Number of Openings: 1  Salary Range: $26.00 - $27.00 per hour (how we pay and promote)  Responsibilities  Write well-designed, testable, efficient code by using best software development practices Use internet technologies, techniques, scripting and object-oriented languages and databases (e.g. HTML, CSS, PHP, MySQL) to create, edit, and update web page elements such as user interface features, site animation, web apps, special effects, databases, and e-business applications Integrate data from various back-end services and databases Troubleshoot a variety of issues including script and plugin errors, media integration, and website usability Support the maintenance, expansion, and scaling of websites Improve websites using industry best practices for both functionality and search engine results Stay plugged into emerging technologies/industry trends and apply them into operations and activities Draft and maintain software documentation Other duties, as assigned   Requirements  Minimum Education and Experience  Bachelor''s degree Enrolled in current graduate program Basic Requirements  Proficient in WordPress and Drupal Excellent documentation skills including with requirements gathering Programming skills and knowledge of modern HTML/CSS Ability to code in at least one programming language, such as Javascript and Python Knowledge of jQuery and other web development libraries and frameworks Basic knowledge of Search Engine Optimization process Strong organizational skills to juggle multiple tasks within the constraints of timelines Ability to work and thrive in a fast-paced environment, learn rapidly, and master diverse web technologies and techniques Highly organized, efficient, and extremely detail-oriented Demonstrated strength in oral and written communication skills, including professional emails Ability to work productively and collaboratively in SharePoint to accomplish tasks Available to support projects for at least 10 hours per week, during 9-5pm Monday-Friday To be successful at Ripple Effect, you must be able to pay attention to details, clearly communicate, work independently, and have an eagerness to learn. Learn more about what makes Ripple so great check out our capabilities. Skills That Set You Apart  Experience with designing, implementing, or maintaining APIs Experience incorporating AI tools into websites for chatbots and other uses If you don''t have all of the skills above, don''t be discouraged—no resume paints a complete picture of a person. There''s a good chance you''re more wonderful than you think, so please apply! About Ripple Effect Ripple Effect is an award-winning women-owned small business providing professional consulting and exceptional talent for federal, private, and non-profit clients. We deliver multi-disciplinary solutions across Communications & Outreach, Research & Evaluation, Program Management & Policy, Digital Transformation, and Technical & Scientific Support solutions with a focus on science, research, and healthcare domains. Hiring Process | Life at Ripple | DEIA   Benefits  Ripple Effect rewards our employees for their contributions to our mission in many ways, from competitive pay and exceptional benefits to a range of work/life programs based on your employment classification and personalized preferences. ----------------------------------------------------------------------- Ripple Effect is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity, political affiliation, or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation during the hiring process, please let us know by contacting our HR department at HR@rippleeffect.com or your recruiter. Eligibility for employment will be verified using E-verify. ', 'https://apply.workable.com/j/DFC691BB80?src=LinkedIn&utm_source=linkedin.com&src=LinkedIn&src=LinkedIn&utm_source=linkedin.com&gh_src=i5qg2y1&utm_source=linkedin.com', 180, 73);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (253, 'Senior Data Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-07 22:49:45', 'LISTED', 'Position: Senior Data Engineer Location: RemoteWe are looking for a skilled Senior Data Engineer to lead the management and optimization of our data storage solutions, focusing on advanced vector databases and data stores such as Elastic Search and AWS OpenSearch. The ideal candidate will have expertise in cloud infrastructure and Site Reliability Engineering (SRE) practices, with proven experience in guiding data infrastructure migrations. This role is crucial for maintaining the performance, reliability, and scalability of our data systems. Key Responsibilities:Manage and optimize vector databases and data stores, specifically Elastic Search and AWS OpenSearch.Lead the migration and upgrade of data infrastructure to modern, scalable solutions.Ensure high availability, performance, and scalability of data systems on cloud platforms such as AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud.Apply SRE methodologies to enhance system reliability and performance.Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand data requirements and deliver tailored data solutions.Monitor, optimize, and maintain data storage and retrieval processes for efficiency.Troubleshoot and resolve complex issues within the data infrastructure.Create and maintain detailed documentation for data systems and workflows. Required Skills and Experience:Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field.5+ years of experience managing and optimizing vector databases and data stores, with a strong focus on Elastic Search and AWS OpenSearch.Solid experience with cloud platforms such as AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud.Familiarity with Site Reliability Engineering (SRE) practices to enhance system resilience.Proven track record of leading data infrastructure migrations.Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to address complex infrastructure issues.Excellent understanding of data architecture and best practices in data management.Effective communication skills, with the ability to work collaboratively with diverse teams. Preferred Qualifications:Master’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field.Experience with additional data stores and databases.Certifications in cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, Google Cloud).Familiarity with automation tools and scripting languages. This position offers an opportunity for a Senior Data Engineer to drive the optimization of advanced data infrastructure within a dynamic, growth-oriented environment. If you have a passion for data reliability, scalability, and innovation, we’d love to connect with you.', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4067840170', 181, 1);
