INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (269, 'Data Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-10-25 19:07:04', 'LISTED', 'Summary/ObjectiveAURA is seeking a talented Data Engineer to join our Data and Software Engineering team. We are looking for a hands-on professional who is self-driven and highly motivated, with a strong sense of initiative and an entrepreneurial mindset. The ideal candidate will have proven experience in applying engineering principles, utilizing the scientific method, and employing deductive reasoning to effectively solve problems. A key skill is the ability to isolate and control independent variables in complex scenarios to drive optimal solutions. You will be part of a cross functional team that is growing, fast-paced, and fun. Most importantly, you will have ownership of and responsibility for delivering solutions that exceed our customers’ expectations. You are a dynamic engineer, always working backwards from customers’ needs, ready to tackle new challenges and learn. You enjoy working in a diverse team, with engineers from many backgrounds and disciplines.Primary Job ResponsibilitiesDesign, build, and maintain scalable data pipelines and ETL processes to support data integration from various sources.Develop, implement, and optimize data architectures using AWS services (e.g., S3, Redshift, Glue, Lambda, Athena, etc.).Collaborate with data scientists, analysts, and other stakeholders to understand data needs and ensure data availability and quality.Monitor and troubleshoot data pipelines to ensure data accuracy, performance, and reliability.Participate in code reviews, testing, and continuous integration processes to ensure high-quality deliverables.Document data engineering processes, data models, and technical specifications.Stay up to date with the latest AWS services and data engineering trends to improve processes and performance.Manage your work in JIRA, tracking utilization and velocity, participate in quarterly and sprint planningCompetencies, Sk