INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (297, 'Data Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-04 21:33:45', 'LISTED', 'Data EngineerRemote (USA)$150, 000 base + benefits  **No H1B sponsorship** - US only People in AI are collaborating with a cutting-edge healthcare tech company to find an experienced Data Engineer. This client is dedicated to leveraging data to drive impactful solutions across the healthcare industry, and they are looking for a skilled engineer with a strong background in Azure, Snowflake, DBT, and Airflow to join their team. About the Role: As a Data Engineer, you’ll play a crucial role in building and optimizing data infrastructure that supports the delivery of critical healthcare insights. You’ll design, implement, and manage data pipelines and workflows within a close-knit engineering team, enabling scalable and efficient data integration. Key Responsibilities: Data Pipeline Development: Design, build, and maintain ETL/ELT pipelines using Airflow to orchestrate workflows and ensure smooth, automated data processes.Data Transformation & Modeling: Use DBT (data build tool) to transform raw data into actionable insights, create robust models, and enhance data quality.Data Management & Storage: Work with Snowflake for efficient data warehousing and handle large data volumes in a highly optimized and secure environment.Cloud Infrastructure: Develop data solutions within Azure, leveraging cloud capabilities to streamline data processing, storage, and accessibility. Ideal Candidate Profile: Experience: 3+ years in data engineering, with proven expertise in Azure, DBT, Snowflake, and Airflow.Technical Expertise: Strong command of SQL and Python for data manipulation and scripting, with a deep understanding of best practices in data pipeline design.Collaboration & Communication: Effective at working with cross-functional teams, understanding data needs, and translating them into practical solutions.Problem-Solving Mindset: Skilled at troubleshooting complex data issues and optimizing workflows for efficiency and scalability. Why Join? Be part of a mission-driven team using data engineering to make a meaningful impact in healthcare. If you’re passionate about cutting-edge data solutions and want to help shape healthcare analytics, we’d love to hear from you!', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4064856781', 209, 1);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (278, 'Full Stack Engineer (Remote)', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-07 21:31:02', 'LISTED', 'Our client is seeking a skilled and dynamic Full Stack Software Engineer to join their team. This role will be responsible for designing, building, and maintaining both the frontend and backend components of their web applications, ensuring a seamless and robust user experience. You will collaborate closely with cross-functional teams to build scalable solutions and deliver high-quality software that supports our business goals. Responsibilities: Build and manage web applications, ensuring they are secure, responsive, and optimized for performance across various devices and browsers.Create and maintain RESTful APIs for seamless communication between front-end and back-end systems.Design, implement, and optimize database structures to support application requirements.Work closely with other engineers, product managers, and designers to understand requirements and translate them into technical solutions.Write clean, maintainable code, conduct peer reviews, and adhere to best practices for coding and documentation.Identify and resolve technical issues throughout the stack, ensuring application reliability and uptime.Keep up-to-date with industry trends, emerging technologies, and best practices in full stack development. Qualifications: B.S. or higher in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field, or equivalent experience.3+ years of experience in full stack development, with proficiency in both frontend and backend technologies.Proficiency in HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and frameworks like React, Angular, or Vue.Strong understanding of server-side languages like Node.js, Python, Ruby, or Java.Experience with SQL (e.g., PostgreSQL, MySQL) and/or NoSQL (e.g., MongoDB) databases.Experience with RESTful APIs and, optionally, GraphQL.Familiarity with CI/CD, cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud), and containerization (Docker, Kubernetes) is a plus.Proficiency in Git and collaborative workflows.Strong problem-solving abilities and attention to detail.Excellent communication skills and a collaborative mindset.Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and adapt to changing requirements. Perks: Remote from within the U.S.Base salary up to 165KUp to 15% Annual bonus401(k) with 100% company match for first 3%Excellent health benefits3 Wks. PTO + Major U.S. Holidays  For a list of all Gyga Force openings, please visit www.gygaforce.com.', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4067831658', 198, 1);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (279, 'Part-Time Senior Front-End Software Engineer (Contract)', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-08 00:40:53', 'LISTED', 'About Us  Parsley Health is a digital health company with a mission to transform the health of everyone, everywhere with the world''s best possible medicine. Today, Parsley Health is the nation''s largest health care company helping people suffering from chronic conditions find relief with root cause resolution medicine. Our work is inspired by our members’ journeys and our actions are focused on impact and results.  The Opportunity  We’re looking for a frontend engineer with experience across multiple technologies and can help the team build exciting new features to support the Parsley Health mission. You will be joining a remote team of passionate engineers reporting into one of our engineering leaders. In this role, you will work closely with engineering, product, design and customer reliability teams. Parsley Health is an outcome driven organization and your work will directly contribute to the company objectives: expand the business nationally, improve activation, conversion, retention, and expansion of our healthcare products.  We work in a blameless environment and we take ownership and pride in our efforts. We like to work in small cross functional product pods where each pod owns the development lifecycle of their products. We follow agile development practices and encourage each pod to tailor the processes to their needs. Our teams are built on pillars of trust, humility and continuous improvement.  This is a part-time contract position, with a commitment of up to 15 hours per week.  What You’ll Do  Build modern, beautiful web applications that shape our members’ experiences, empower doctors and health coaches, and support our internal teamWork closely with our Product and Design teams to develop new products and featuresDesign, spec and estimate tasks to help fit the sprint goals.Participate in code reviews to ensure high code quality and set best practices  What You’ll Need  Deep understanding of frontend architecture and improving build processes (npm, yarn, webpack, parcel)A front-end developer with 5+ years of experience in ReactExperienced with TYpescript, unit testing and GraphQLSomeone who takes a disciplined approach to development, testing, documentation, and code structure in a team environment.  Parsley Health is committed to providing an equitable, fair and transparent compensation program for all employees.  The pay rate for this role is between $120-$140 per hour, depending on skills and experience. We take a geo-neutral approach to compensation within the US, meaning that we pay based on job function and level, not location.  Individual compensation decisions are based on a number of factors, including experience level, skillset, and balancing internal equity relative to peers at the company. We expect the majority of the candidates who are offered roles at our company to fall healthily throughout the range based on these factors. We recognize that the person we hire may be less experienced (or more senior) than this job description as posted. If that ends up being the case, the updated salary range will be communicated with candidates during the process.  At Parsley Health we believe in celebrating everything that makes us human and are proud to be an equal opportunity workplace. We embrace diversity and are committed to building a team that represents a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and skills. We believe that the more inclusive we are, the better we can serve our members.  Important Note  In light of recent increase in hiring scams, if you''re selected to move onto the next phase of our hiring process, a member of our Talent Acquisition team will reach out to you directly from an @parsleyhealth.com email address to guide you through our interview process.  Please Note  We will never communicate with you via Microsoft TeamsWe will never ask for your bank account information at any point during the recruitment process, nor will we send you a check (electronic or physical) to purchase home office equipment  We look forward to connecting!  ', 'https://boards.greenhouse.io/parsleyhealth/jobs/6266907003?gh_src=49d9a7893us', 199, 16);
