 that are highly valued by employers. Build a portfolio that demonstrates your proficiency in modern development practices.Cutting-Edge Technologies: Learn to work with the latest frameworks, tools, and technologies used in full-stack development, DevOps, and cloud computing to stay ahead in the tech industry.Career Advancement: The demand for skilled software engineers is rising across industries. By completing this program, you’ll gain the skills needed to pursue a career as a Software Engineer, Full-Stack Developer, Backend Developer, or DevOps Engineer.Expert Mentorship: Receive guidance from seasoned software engineers who will help you navigate your learning journey and provide insights into industry best practices, career development, and cutting-edge technologies. Apply Today:Ready to take your software engineering skills to the next level? Apply now and join the Software Engineering Mastery Program to gain the experience and expertise needed to unlock exciting career opportunities in software development, system design, and DevOps. Learn More: https://www.refontelearning.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4074607660', 57, 1);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (288, 'Cloud Engineer', false, '', '2024-10-28 22:31:11', 'LISTED', 'The Select Group is seeking an experienced Cloud Engineer to join our telecommunications client’s team in Littleton, CO. This position will require the candidate to work onsite five days a week, Monday through Friday. As a Cloud Engineer, you will be responsible for supporting cloud migration initiatives, managing containerized environments, and ensuring the ongoing optimization and automation of cloud infrastructure.  Cloud Engineer Required Skills  6+ years in information technology in roles such as systems engineer, DevOps, or related.Linux Expertise: Strong proficiency with Linux systems, including system administration, troubleshooting, and performance tuning.Kubernetes/Container Orchestration: Hands-on experience with Kubernetes and container orchestration platforms, managing containerized environments at scale.Cloud Architecture and Virtualization: Solid understanding of cloud infrastructure, including design principles, cloud-native architecture, and virtualization technologies.Python: Proficiency in Python scripting for automation and management tasks.Automation: Experience with Ansible or similar automation tools for infrastructure as code (IaC) and configuration management.Container as a Service (CaaS): Familiarity with CaaS models for managing containers in the cloud.CI/CD Pipelines: Experience designing and building CI/CD pipelines for efficient deployment and integration in cloud environments.  Cloud Engineer Responsibilities  Support and drive the migration of workloads from VMware to cloud environments while ensuring minimal service disruption and platform stability.Develop and manage CI/CD pipelines to automate the deployment process and improve development workflows.Work with cross-functional teams to ensure a smooth transition of data and applications to the cloud.Maintain and optimize Kubernetes clusters and other container orchestration systems.