INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (293, 'AWS Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-10-31 23:03:48', 'LISTED', 'The AWS engineer will provide strategic counsel and advice to top management on significant engineering matters, overseeing the design and development of a consolidated enterprise data warehouse and data lake. This role involves managing highly complex processes that impact the organization, leading sizable projects, and delivering an enterprise information environment for strategic decision-making capabilities. The ideal candidate will provide thought leadership and technical expertise across multiple disciplines, serving as the go-to person for complex Information Management assignments. The ideal candidate should have extensive experience in Engineering and Data Management, with a track record of providing strategic counsel to top management. They should have expertise in designing and developing enterprise data warehouses and data lakes, managing complex processes, and leading sizable projects. This AWS Engineer will be asked to create, maintain, and evolve an AWS cloud infrastructure for running applications with a strong emphasis on reliability and resiliency. Strong analytical skills, problem-solving abilities, and the ability to sift through large amounts of data to find relationships and patterns are crucial. The candidate should be recognized internally as a thought leader and technical expert in Information Management. Role Responsibilities:· Provide strategic counsel on engineering matters· Design and development of enterprise data warehouse and data lake· Process management for complex projects· Data analysis and pattern recognition· Leading and managing sizable projects· Participating in the delivery of an enterprise information environment for strategic decision-making capabilities· Focusing on providing thought leadership and technical expertise across multiple disciplines· Being recognized internally as the go-to person for complex Information Management assignments Required Experience and Skills:· 7+ years in a software engineering environment· 5+ years AWS Administrator, EKS, CLI, Helmchart, Cloudwatch.· In depth understanding and knowledge of Rest Web Services, Micro Services and CI/CD. · Ability to work in SCRUM based Agile teams and practice Agile methodologies and ceremonies.· Must demonstrate strong skills in communication, problem solving, collaboration, leadership and project management.  Preferred Skills:· Experience with PRPC 7.x or PRPC 8.x, HCIF and/or other Pega solutions with Pega CSSA, CSA certification holders· Project leadership experience; Thought leadership in Information Management· Expertise in objected-oriented techniques/principles, system integration using web services and service interfaces, database design', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4063737530', 9, 1);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (300, 'FREELANCE | PHP Developer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-04 14:04:28', 'LISTED', 'Our dynamic and innovative team at BarkleyOKRP is looking for a developer to support our internal team as needs arise. We are a leading advertising agency dedicated to delivering exceptional web solutions for our diverse range of clients. With a wide variety of projects, you''ll always find new challenges and opportunities to learn.  We are seeking a talented and motivated PHP Developer to work alongside our development team. This is an excellent opportunity for someone looking to advance their web development capabilities and gain valuable experience in a fast-paced agency. You will work on various web development projects, collaborating with designers, project managers, and other developers to create and maintain high-quality websites.  Responsibilities:  Develop, test, and maintain PHP-based websites.Implement websites using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and jQuery.Collaborate with the team to design and implement new features and enhancements.Utilize version control systems, particularly Git.Ensure code quality and adherence to best practices through code reviews and testing.Work independently on tasks, managing time effectively to meet deadlines.Embrace continuous learning challenges with new tasks and technologies.  Required Qualifications:  3+ years of experience with PHP development.Basic understanding of CMS principles.Experience with source control management using Git.Proficiency in implementing websites with HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and jQuery.Experience providing freelance or contract support preferred.Strong willingness to learn and adapt to new challenges.  Nice to Have:  Experience with various CMSs, such as Drupal and WordPress.Familiarity with PHP template engines, such as TWIG.Ability to debug and optimize PHP applications for better performance.Experience with database design, optimization, and management, particularly MySQL.  BarkleyOKRP''s Commitment to Diversity & Inclusion  We believe being radically diverse and inclusive is the key to becoming one of the world''s great creative idea companies. By embracing everything that makes our partners who they are and what makes them unique to the world around them, we create the conditions and capacity to help creative, original thinking thrive. BarkleyOKRP is committed to Diversity, Equity, Inclusion and Belonging as part of our corporate strategic goals, supported by a formal DEI+B program, Employee Resource Groups, Director of Diversity leadership and agency commitment to The Brand Lab, Creative Accelerator, Fellowship, MAIP, and BLAC.', 'https://grnh.se/e3ac91eb4us', 211, 83);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (301, 'Sr. Data Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-10-28 15:03:34', 'LISTED', 'Title: Sr. Data Engineer Location:  Remote- EST Duration:  22 Month Contract Compensation: $90-$95/hr Work Requirements: US Citizen, GC Holders or Authorized to Work in the US   We are seeking an experienced AI/LLM Data Engineer to build and maintain the data pipeline for our Generative AI platform. The ideal candidate will be well-versed in the latest Large Language Model (LLM) technologies and have a strong background in data engineering, with a focus on Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) and knowledge-base techniques. This role sits in the AI COE. As a AI/LLM Data Engineer (you will report into the Director, AI Solutions & Development who oversees the AI COE.  You will work on highly visible strategic projects, collaborating with cross-functional teams to define requirements and deliver high-quality AI solutions. The ideal candidate will have a passion for Generative AI and LLMs, with a proven track record of delivering innovative AI applications.  Responsibilities:Design, implement, and maintain an end-to-end multi-stage data pipeline for LLMs, including Supervised Fine Tuning (SFT) and Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF) data processesIdentify, evaluate, and integrate diverse data sources and domains to support the Generative AI platformDevelop and optimize data processing workflows for chunking, indexing, ingestion, and vectorization for both text and non-text dataBenchmark and implement various vector stores, embedding techniques, and retrieval methodsCreate a flexible pipeline supporting multiple embedding algorithms, vector stores, and search types (e.g., vector search, hybrid search)Implement and maintain auto-tagging systems and data preparation processes for LLMsDevelop tools for text and image data crawling, cleaning, and refinementCollaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure data quality and relevance for AI/ML modelsWork with data lake house architectures to optimize data storage and processingIntegrate and optimize workflows using Snowflake and various vector store technologies  Skillset / Experience:Master''s deg in Computer Science, Data Science, etc3-5 years of work experience in data engineering, preferably in AI/ML contextsProficiency in Python, JSON, HTTP, and related toolsStrong understanding of LLM architectures, training processes, and data requirementsExperience with RAG systems, knowledge base construction, and vector databasesFamiliarity with embedding techniques, similarity search algorithms, and information retrieval conceptsHands-on experience with data cleaning, tagging, and annotation processes (both manual and automated)Knowledge of data crawling techniques and associated ethical considerationsStrong problem-solving skills and ability to work in a fast-paced, innovative environmentFamiliarity with Snowflake and its integration in AI/ML pipelinesExperience with various vector store technologies and their applications in AIUnderstanding of data lakehouse concepts and architecturesExcellent communication, collaboration, and problem-solving skills.Ability to translate business needs into technical solutions.Passion for innovation and a commitment to ethical AI development.Experience building LLMs pipeline using framework like LangChain, LlamaIndex, Semantic Kernel, OpenAI functions.Familiar with different LLM parameters like temperate, top-k, and repeat penalty, and different LLM outcome evaluation data science metrics and methodologies.Nice to Have:Experience with popular LLM/ RAG frameworksFamiliarity with distributed computing platforms (e.g., Apache Spark, Dask)Knowledge of data versioning and experiment tracking toolsExperience with cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, or Azure) for large-scale data processingUnderstanding of data privacy and security best practicesPractical experience implementing data lakehouse solutionsProficiency in optimizing queries and data processes