INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (305, 'AI & Data Scientist Intern', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-12 17:43:51', 'LISTED', 'Join Refonte AI''s Global Internship Program in AI, Data Science, DevOps, and Cloud About Refonte AIRefonte AI is a premier global IT and Ed-tech provider known for delivering high-quality services in Artificial Intelligence (AI), data science, digital marketing, data analytics, UI/UX design, web and app development. We prioritize innovation, excellence, and talent development worldwide, creating meaningful solutions for businesses and individuals. Learn More and Apply: https://refontelearning.com Position: AI, Data Science, DevOps, and Cloud Intern Location:Remote (USA-based) Why Join Us?Our internship offers a valuable chance to gain hands-on experience in cutting-edge technologies, including AI, Data Science, DevOps, and Cloud. Interns will work on impactful, real-world projects, enhancing their skills and knowledge alongside industry experts. If you’re passionate about technology and ready to learn, this is the opportunity for you! Job SummaryRefonte AI invites motivated individuals to participate in our prestigious AI & Data Science Study and Internship Program. This program combines comprehensive training with hands-on experience in live projects across various industries. You''ll collaborate with experts and a global team from Oceania, Asia, Europe, and the Americas, all within a flexible, supportive work environment. Position OverviewThis internship is tailored for individuals passionate about AI, Data Science, DevOps, and Cloud technologies. As an intern, you will gain hands-on experience in these interconnected fields, participating in innovative projects and working alongside industry leaders to develop practical solutions. Key ResponsibilitiesCollaborate with cross-functional teams to build, deploy, and maintain AI-powered solutions.Assist in collecting, cleaning, and analyzing data to derive actionable insights.Contribute to designing scalable data pipelines for model training and deployment.Support the integration of machine learning models into production using DevOps best practices.Develop CI/CD pipelines for AI applications on cloud platforms.Configure, provision, and monitor cloud infrastructure using AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud.Partner with data scientists and engineers to align technical solutions with business goals.Explore new tools and technologies in AI, Data Science, DevOps, and Cloud.Document processes and knowledge to promote best practices within the team. Exciting Projects You’ll Work OnMulti-Cloud AI Infrastructure: Configure, automate, and deploy AI solutions across multiple cloud platforms.Full Stack AI DevOps & Development: Engage in comprehensive DevOps for AI projects.Generative AI Models: Work with cutting-edge models to transform input types (text, images, audio, video) into various outputs.Financial Fraud Detection: Design algorithms to detect fraud using advanced data analysis.Recommender Systems: Contribute to personalized recommendation systems for improved user experience.Sentiment Analysis: Analyze textual data to uncover insights and enhance sentiment understanding.Chatbots: Build intelligent chatbots for customer support.Multimedia Classification: Classify images, audio, and video with advanced AI technology.Text Analysis: Explore sophisticated techniques to detect patterns in textual data. Roles & Learning OpportunitiesPartner with our AI & Data Science team to gather, preprocess, and visualize data.Assist in building predictive models using advanced machine learning techniques.Collaborate with team members to design, execute, and evaluate experiments.Stay informed on the latest trends and best practices in AI and Data Science. EligibilityCurrently pursuing a degree, with a keen interest in continual learning.Strong written and verbal communication skills.Ability to work both independently and within a team, demonstrating adaptability and a collaborative spirit. Internship BenefitsGain practical experience in AI, Data Science, DevOps, and Cloud technologies.Collaborate on impactful projects and build your portfolio.Work in a dynamic, global team that promotes learning and growth. Note: This is an unpaid internship through our AI & Data Science Study and Internship Program. Once you apply, our team will follow up with details on the application and onboarding process. Learn More and Apply: https://refontelearning.com Location:Remote (USA-based) Thank you for considering Refonte AI for your professional journey in data science. We look forward to welcoming you to our global team!', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4075013212', 57, 1);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (306, 'Full-Time Contract Senior Front-End Software Engineer (Spain)', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-12 00:41:42', 'LISTED', 'About Us  Parsley Health is a digital health company with a mission to transform the health of everyone, everywhere with the world''s best possible medicine. Today, Parsley Health is the nation''s largest health care company helping people suffering from chronic conditions find relief with root cause resolution medicine. Our work is inspired by our members’ journeys and our actions are focused on impact and results.  The Opportunity  We’re looking for a frontend engineer with experience across multiple technologies and can help the team build exciting new features to support the Parsley Health mission. You will be joining a remote team of passionate engineers reporting into one of our engineering leaders. In this role, you will work closely with engineering, product, design and customer reliability teams. Parsley Health is an outcome driven organization and your work will directly contribute to the company objectives: expand the business nationally, improve activation, conversion, retention, and expansion of our healthcare products.  We work in a blameless environment and we take ownership and pride in our efforts. We like to work in small cross functional product pods where each pod owns the development lifecycle of their products. We follow agile development practices and encourage each pod to tailor the processes to their needs. Our teams are built on pillars of trust, humility and continuous improvement.  This is a full-time contract position with a commitment of 40 hours/week.  What You’ll Do  Build modern, beautiful web applications that shape our members’ experiences, empower doctors and health coaches, and support our internal teamWork closely with our Product and Design teams to develop new products and featuresDesign, spec and estimate tasks to help fit the sprint goals.Participate in code reviews to ensure high code quality and set best practices  What You’ll Need  Deep understanding of frontend architecture and improving build processes (npm, yarn, webpack, parcel)A front-end developer with 5+ years of experience in ReactExperienced with TYpescript, unit testing and GraphQLSomeone who takes a disciplined approach to development, testing, documentation, and code structure in a team environment.  Parsley Health is committed to providing an equitable, fair and transparent compensation program for all employees.  The pay rate for this role is $8, 000 per month, depending on skills and experience. We take a geo-neutral approach to compensation within the US, meaning that we pay based on job function and level, not location.  Individual compensation decisions are based on a number of factors, including experience level, skillset, and balancing internal equity relative to peers at the company. We expect the majority of the candidates who are offered roles at our company to fall healthily throughout the range based on these factors. We recognize that the person we hire may be less experienced (or more senior) than this job description as posted. If that ends up being the case, the updated salary range will be communicated with candidates during the process.  At Parsley Health we believe in celebrating everything that makes us human and are proud to be an equal opportunity workplace. We embrace diversity and are committed to building a team that represents a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and skills. We believe that the more inclusive we are, the better we can serve our members.  Important Note  In light of recent increase in hiring scams, if you''re selected to move onto the next phase of our hiring process, a member of our Talent Acquisition team will reach out to you directly from an @parsleyhealth.com email address to guide you through our interview process.  Please Note  We will never communicate with you via Microsoft TeamsWe will never ask for your bank account information at any point during the recruitment process, nor will we send you a check (electronic or physical) to purchase home office equipment  We look forward to connecting!  ', 'https://boards.greenhouse.io/parsleyhealth/jobs/6266948003?gh_src=49d9a7893us', 199, 16);
