INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (317, 'Systems Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-06 22:28:42', 'LISTED', 'TITLE: Systems Engineer JOB TYPE: Full Time Remote  JOB DESCRIPTION The Systems Engineer role serves as a “hands on” subject matter expert for a large, diverse, and complex project in the Hyperscale Data Center industry, performing modeling of data center environments. This role requires excellent communication, organization, and critical thinking skills. The applicant must be well organized, perform tasks with precision and attention to detail.  Specific responsibilities include:  Performs measurements and calculations necessary to model data center environments in an in-house data center management system. Obtains data from various systems, performing data transformation as necessary in tools such as Microsoft Excel to import in an in-house data center management system. Serves as a subject matter expert for their assigned product/project capable of performing demonstrations and explaining features and benefits. Works directly with end customer representatives to understand their organization at all facets (business model, processes, and users) and translate their requirements for the internal software development team, as necessary. Engages actively in the software development lifecycle for the system, performing quality assurance activities as required to ensure quality product delivery. SKILLS AND ABILITIES  Self-starter with ability to meet timelines with minimal supervision. Analytical and mathematical mind, capable of evaluating and solving various complex problems, yet biased to action. Excellent written and verbal communication skills. Demonstrates a positive team spirit with collaboration, feedback, mentoring, and coaching. Attention to customer-first ideology driving customer delight. Able to prioritize and handle multiple tasks/projects simultaneously. Demonstrates “can-do” attitude, organization, and time management skills. Resourceful ability to solve problems quickly and efficiently. Delivery using iterative methodology and standard tools and processes.  REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS  MS Office 365 experience, specifically Microsoft Excel. Demonstrated ability to take initiative, prioritize work, manage time, and respond effectively to a rapidly changing environment. PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS  Knowledge of the Data Center and/or Telecommunications industry. Experience performing “take off” measurements from drawings. Prior experience reviewing technical drawings such as electrical drawings, floor plans and cable tray layout diagrams. Experience obtaining scaled measurements using BlueBeam Revu, Fox It PDF and/or Adobe Acroba.t  EDUCATION/CERTIFICATION  A Bachelor’s degree or an equivalent combination of education and relevant experience preferred, but not required.', 'https://geopaqlogic.oorwin.com/careers/index.html#/job/4260e7eabc193825e5a09c31c41d9c739703be50?source=linkedin_free&postedby=14', 223, 1);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (318, 'Full Stack Development Training and Internship Program', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-12 04:17:42', 'LISTED', 'Program Title: Full Stack Development Training and Internship (M/F)Location: RemoteProgram Type: Training with Practical InternshipDuration: 3 monthsCompensation: Unpaid Learn More : https://www.refontelearning.com/ Program Overview:The Full Stack Development Internship and Training Program is designed to provide you with a comprehensive learning experience in both front-end and back-end web development. This program is ideal for aspiring web developers looking to build a solid foundation in JavaScript, React, Node.js, Express, and Databases. You will have the opportunity to apply what you learn on real-world projects, enhancing your portfolio and gaining invaluable practical experience in the process. Program Objectives:Learn Front-End Technologies: Gain in-depth knowledge of HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript, as well as frameworks like React and Vue.js to build dynamic user interfaces.Back-End Development: Master Node.js, Express, and how to build RESTful APIs to manage server-side logic.Database Management: Learn how to integrate SQL and NoSQL databases (like MongoDB and MySQL) into your web applications for efficient data management.Project-Based Learning: Collaborate with cross-functional teams on real client projects, contributing to both front-end and back-end components of full-stack applications.Agile Development: Work in Agile teams, gaining exposure to industry practices, sprint cycles, and code reviews. Skills You Will Develop:In-depth understanding of front-end frameworks like React and Vue.js for building modern, scalable user interfaces.Practical experience with back-end frameworks like Node.js and Express for building scalable server-side applications.Knowledge of RESTful API development, and database integration with MongoDB, MySQL, and PostgreSQL.Familiarity with Git and Version Control for managing code collaboration and deployment.Proficiency in building responsive web designs and ensuring cross-browser compatibility.Hands-on experience in Agile development environments and team collaboration. Who Should Apply:Graduates and students with a keen interest in pursuing a career in web development, software engineering, or full stack development.Software developers or IT professionals looking to upgrade their skills in front-end and back-end technologies.Anyone eager to build web applications and learn new technologies in a dynamic, real-world setting. Why You Should Join:Practical Exposure: Work directly on projects from concept to deployment, building real-world applications that you can showcase in your portfolio.Learning from Experts: Receive mentorship and feedback from industry professionals to accelerate your career in full-stack development.Career Pathways: Upon successful completion, you’ll be equipped to pursue roles like Full Stack Developer, Front-End Developer, or Back-End Developer.Global Network: Join an international team of developers and gain experience collaborating with professionals across different time zones. Learn More : https://www.refontelearning.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4074382335', 57, 1);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (319, 'Jr. Software Development Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-04 13:55:01', 'LISTED', 'Who is Blueprint?  We are a technology solutions firm headquartered in Bellevue, Washington, with a strong presence across the United States. Unified by a shared passion for solving complicated problems, our people are our greatest asset. We use technology as a tool to bridge the gap between strategy and execution, powered by the knowledge, skills, and the expertise of our teams, who all have unique perspectives and years of experience across multiple industries. We''re bold, smart, agile, and fun.  What does Blueprint do?  Blueprint helps organizations unlock value from existing assets by leveraging cutting-edge technology to create additional revenue streams and new lines of business. We connect strategy, business solutions, products, and services to transform and grow companies.  Why Blueprint?  At Blueprint, we believe in the power of possibility and are passionate about bringing it to life. Whether you join our bustling product division, our multifaceted services team or you want to grow your career, your ability to make an impact is amplified when you join one of our teams. You''ll focus on solving unique business problems while gaining hands-on experience with the world''s best technology. We believe in unique perspectives and build teams of people with diverse skillsets and backgrounds. At Blueprint, you''ll have the opportunity to work with multiple clients and teams, such as data science and product development, all while learning, growing, and developing new solutions. We guarantee you won''t find a better place to work and thrive than at Blueprint.  We are looking for a Jr. Software Development Engineer to join us as we build cutting-edge technology solutions! This is your opportunity to be part of a team that is committed to delivering best-in-class service to our customers.  In this role you will contribute to the development, deployment, and maintenance of our Azure-based reinforcement learning loop project. The ideal candidate will have experience with Azure deployment, CICD processes, and C#/app development/debugging. They will play a crucial role in packaging components, ensuring compliance, automating processes, and providing documentation for seamless project integration.  Responsibilities:  Package the reinforcement learning loop component in a Docker image or similar mechanism. Publish the packaged component to a public container registry like Azure Container Registry. Ensure compliance with internal release tracker process and certification for public release.Publish Bicep scripts to create related resources for deploying the image in Azure subscriptions. Open-source the repository for the component following Microsoft''s open-source process. Create comprehensive documentation for easy project consumption. Perform system runs, conduct sanity checks, performance tests, and troubleshoot issues.   Qualifications:  Bachelor''s degree in computer science, software engineering, or a relevant field required. Minimum of 2 years of experience in software development and deployment. Verbal and written communication skills, problem-solving skills, customer service, and interpersonal skills. Ability to work independently and manage time effectively. Package C# components, build container images, and automate related processes. Basic troubleshooting skills and the ability to make system changes to resolve issues. Basic knowledge of computer hardware and software. Proficiency in C#, Docker, CI/CD, Azure services (EventHub, Storage, AKS), and Azure deployment tools (Bicep, ARM, identity).  Preferred Qualifications:  Familiarity with Bicep scripting language.   Salary Range  Pay ranges vary based on multiple factors including, without limitation, skill sets, education, responsibilities, experience, and geographical market. The pay range for this position reflects geographic based ranges for Washington state: $80, 000 - $87, 000 USD/annually. The salary/wage and job title for this opening will be based on the selected candidate''s qualifications and experience and may be outside this range.  Equal Opportunity Employer  Blueprint Technologies, LLC is an equal employment opportunity employer. Qualified applicants are considered without regard to race, color, age, disability, sex, gender identity or expression, orientation, veteran/military status, religion, national origin, ancestry, marital, or familial status, genetic information, citizenship, or any other status protected by law.  If you need assistance or a reasonable accommodation to complete the application process, please reach out to: recruiting@bpcs.com  Blueprint believes in the importance of a healthy and happy team, which is why our comprehensive benefits package includes:  Medical, dental, and vision coverage Flexible Spending Account 401k program Competitive PTO offerings Parental Leave Opportunities for professional growth and development   Location: Remote', 'https://grnh.se/c81a0a5c1us', 224, 32);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (320, 'Software Developer', true, 'Remote', '2024-10-29 20:18:16', 'LISTED', 'Who is Fusion Technology?  Fusion Technology is a performance-driven HUBZone Small Business concern residing in the heart of the beautiful mountainsides of West Virginia, steps away from the Federal Bureau of Investigation''s Criminal Justice Information Services Division''s Headquarters. Founded in 2007 by an Engineer-by-trade, Fusion Technology dedicates our valuable resources to providing comprehensive IT services and solutions to mission-critical US Government programs and the Intel Community.  Who are you?  Security-cleared Professional:You have made it through the process of receiving a United States government security clearance – congratulations! We know you are a trustworthy intel professional because you have an active Secret security clearanceExperience is important to us:You have a Bachelor’s degree with 5 years of experience or an additional 4 years of experience in lieu of degreeExperienced Software Developer:You have experience with Java, Spring, AWS Cloud, Atlassian Suite, CI/CD, XML, SOAP/RESTful web services, Docker/Kubernetes and some DevOps experience in an agile environment  Position location: Remote (occasionaltravel to the main work site for special events)  What you’ll do:  Develop and configure customized software product/system to meet client requirementsBuild and support specialized customizations to the core asset software including conversions, interfaces, enhancements, and user interface modificationsMay include end-to-end software development starting from analysis moving on to design, implementation, QA, delivery, and maintenanceApplies knowledge of technologies, applications, methods, processes, and tools to support a client, project, or entity  What matters to you matters to us.  Fusion Technology values its employees and works hard to ensure proper care for them and their families. We desire to compensate employees in a competitive, motivational, fair, and equitable way with other employers in the marketplace. Salary is only one component of employee compensation but an integral part of recruiting and retaining qualified employees. However, at Fusion Technology, we take a comprehensive approach and consider each employee''s needs to tailor a compensation plan that provides financial security and peace of mind. Our competitive package includes a best-in-class matching 401K program, a comprehensive healthcare plan through Meritain, a competitive employer contribution to a health savings account, vision and dental plans, life insurance, short- and long-term disability, and personal leave, in addition to paid certifications and training.  Fusion Technology LLC is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We respect and seek to empower each individual and support the diverse cultures, perspectives, skills, and experiences within our workforce. Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to sex, race, ethnicity, age, national origin, citizenship, religion, physical or mental disability, medical condition, genetic information, pregnancy, family structure, marital status, ancestry, domestic partner status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, veteran or military status, or any other basis prohibited by law.  Powered by JazzHR  iSqByaCsiV', 'https://fusiontechnologyllc.applytojob.com/apply/iSqByaCsiV/Software-Developer?source=LILI&source=LINKEDIN', 225, 89);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (321, 'DevOps Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-05 00:12:36', 'LISTED', 'Job Title: DevOps EngineerLocation: UtahJob-Type: PermanentSalary Range: $135K – 150K + bonusReferral Fee: $3, 500Employment Eligibility: Gravity cannot transfer nor sponsor a work visa for this position. Applicants must be eligible to work in the U.S. for any employer directly (we are not open to contract or “corp to corp” agreements).Position Overview:Gravity IT is seeking a DevOps Engineer to become a key member of a small and growing DevOps team. In this role, you will wear multiple hats and will be part developer and part infrastructure/operations. You will gather requirements from other technology teams across the organization and with other engineers to translate them into reliable automated infrastructure systems. In this role, you will be a strategic contributor, seeking ways to achieve automation through Infrastructure as Code, Terraform Configuration, and use is CI/CD wherever possible. You will be a major contributor in building platforms that are reliable and scalable.Duties & Responsibilities:· Gather requirements from clients and other engineers working across various projects, ensuring a solid understanding of the big picture and the end goals of the project.· Design and develop the strategies and implementation necessary to produce reliable infrastructure systems according to requirements.· Drive automation using popular cloud orchestration, configuration management, and CI/CD systems.· Help automate management and monitoring systems across all environments.· Help build adaptive and scalable containerized application infrastructure systems using Kubernetes best practices.· Creating infrastructure using repeatable templates and processes demonstrated by tearing them down and bringing them back up again in a safe and repeatable fashion that minimizes manual input.· Use modern automation and configuration management tools to automate DevOps tasks