ocus on Skills-Based hiring. We specialize in placing individuals in roles ranging from entry-level to VP level across various fields, including Customer Success, Sales & Marketing, Finance & Accounting, Administrative, HR, Operations, and Technology. Our expertise spans contract/temporary, temporary-to-permanent, permanent, and payrolling services, and we are dedicated to promoting equitable hiring practices on a national scale.  Please note that compensation for the specific role will be determined based on your unique skills and experience. If you have an interest in exploring other positions similar to this one, please be aware that compensation rates and benefits packages may vary accordingly.We do consider applications from qualified candidates with prior arrests and conviction records, in accordance with applicable regulations.It is imperative that you have the legal authorization to work in the United States, as we do not provide sponsorship.  ', NULL, 234, 32);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (333, 'Software Engineering Mastery Training and Internship Program', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-06 23:45:16', 'LISTED', 'Program Title : Software Engineering Mastery Training and Internship (M/F)Location : RemoteProgram Type : Training with Practical InternshipDuration : 3 monthsCompensation : UnpaidSite web : https://www.refontelearning.com/ Job Description:This DevOps Engineering Trainee role is a structured training and internship program focused on mastering essential DevOps skills. Trainees will receive dedicated mentorship and training in automation, infrastructure management, and cloud technologies. This program offers hands-on experience in building and maintaining CI/CD pipelines, automating workflows, and working in a dynamic DevOps environment. Key Responsibilities:Learn to configure and manage CI/CD pipelines for smooth and secure deployments.Develop automation scripts to optimize deployment and testing processes.Assist in managing cloud infrastructure and maintaining high-security standards. Qualifications:Current student in Computer Science, Information Systems, or a related technical field.Familiarity with cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, Google Cloud) and CI/CD tools (Jenkins, Docker, Kubernetes).Strong analytical skills, a desire to learn, and problem-solving abilities. Skills Developed:Mastery in CI/CD processes, infrastructure automation, and security best practices.Hands-on experience with containerization and cloud resource management.', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4066468151', 235, 95);
