INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (336, 'Data Scientist', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-12 19:48:45', 'LISTED', 'No H1B candidates will be Considered  Must have skills : Elastic Search, Generative AI Fundamentals (Strong), Python for Data Science (Strong), RAG, Vector Illustration Good to have skills:Job Description : Data Scientist with ~6+ years of expertise in Natural Language Processing (NLP), Large Language Models (LLMs), and Generative AI (GenAI).The ideal candidate will have hands-on experience with search-related work, including relevance tuning, text classification, and topic modeling.Additionally, experience in building Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipelines for search and chat applications is highly desired. Key Responsibilities:Develop and optimize NLP models for text classification, text clustering, topic modeling, and relevance tuning in search.Work with LLMs to build advanced generative AI solutions for search and chat applications.Design and implement Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipelines to improve search and conversational AI systems.Collaborate with cross-functional teams to deploy data-driven search enhancements and GenAI solutions.Analyze and fine-tune search relevance based on user behavior and search intent from querylog. Qualifications: Experience in running and fine-tuning models from Hugging faceFamiliarity with building and deploying RAG pipelinesFamiliarity with vector databases like Elasticsearch, Pinecone, etc.Strong programming skills (e.g., Python, TensorFlow, PyTorch, SQL)Experience in model deployment & MLOps is a plusExperience with cloud platforms (AWS) is a plus. ', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4072904864', 236, 1);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (337, 'Full Stack Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-07 22:52:53', 'LISTED', 'The RoleWe are seeking Full Stack Software Engineers with anywhere from 2 to 10+ years of experience to support and help grow our Core Engineering Team, owning all core systems for the business.This includes high-scale, high-availability systems that power all business functions and several customer-facing Admins and UIs. In this role, you will collaborate with engineers and across teams on a broad range of responsibilities. You will help design and develop scalable solutions and help continuously improve the product, practices, and architecture.You will be a prolific contributor to core projects, experimental work, and technically driven initiatives. When presented with a complex problem, process, or existing system, you must consistently demonstrate the ability to reduce complexity, to get more done with less work. About ConfiantWe believe that engineers solve problems end-to-end. From researching the problem to customer interaction, collaboration across design and product management teams, iterating on team processes, and participating in the on-call rotation, engineers are an integral part of our team and own the end-to-end of shipping amazing products to customers. We fundamentally believe that software works better when engineers own the whole lifecycle of solving problems for our customers. We work every day to reflect these beliefs in our culture and teams. We are a 100% virtual company, and all our team members work from home worldwide. We support optional monthly gatherings in New York City (our original home) and quarterly on-sites in various locations across the world in order to maintain the human connection and trust required to be a high-performing organization. About The TeamWe are a small (but growing!) engineering team that strives for high engineering standards, high cross-team and cross-domain collaboration, and continuous improvement. Our tech stack evolves quickly to manage our growing scale and tackle the challenges we take on as a company. We promote ongoing learning, encourage innovation, and enjoy interpersonal communication.We’re a team built remotely. Our team members are spread around the world with various time zones and various cultures. We love the challenge that comes with remote work as much as we enjoy the benefits. Asynchronous communication is common. A desire to work closely with peers and the drive to make great technology is necessary. We manage large scale ETL systems, APIs, and embedded systems that process10s of millions of transactions a day while writing 10/100s of millions of database records a day, solving large scale ingestion, ETL and response problems for some of the largest players in the AdTech space. As a member of our team, you would be an integral part of supporting these and other similar systems. ResponsibilitiesBuild scalable applications with well defined architectural patterns.Rapidly debug production issues.Solve complex technical problems.Collaborate with cross-functional teams.Implement innovative solutions into current and greenfield products. RequirementsDeep knowledge of multiple programming languages, expert in at least one (Python, PHP or Javascript preferred).In depth knowledge of many modern software engineering paradigms and models, including OOD, functional programming, design patterns, etc.Primary focus on backend technologies with experience across various technologies and frameworks (Puppeteer, ReactJS, Symphony, Flask, etc.).Broad understanding of AWS/Cloud Infrastructure and deep specific experience with one or more areas of designing, deploying, and managing cloud infrastructure is preferred.Able to work within 5 hours of EST, either 5 hours ahead or 5 hours behind. Desired ExperienceEngineer II: Minimum of 2+ years of experience and some proven maturity solving complex problems across various technical domains.Engineer III: Minimum of 4+ years of experience and significant maturity solving complex problems across various technical domains, communicating with/through Product and being a force multiplier for more Junior Engineers.Engineer IV: Minimum of 6+ years of experience and significant maturity solving complex problems across various technical domains, communicating with/through Product and being a force multiplier for your engineering team.Engineer V: Minimum of 8+ years of experience and significant maturity solving complex problems across various technical domains, communicating with/through Product and being a force multiplier for your engineering team as well as proven experience in setting engineering practices and principles within a working environment.Engineer VI: Minimum of 10+ years of experience and significant maturity solving complex problems across various technical domains, communicating with/through Product and being a force multiplier for the entire engineering org as well as proven experience owning the evolution of engineering practices and principles within an engineering organization.AdTech or Security experience is a plus, but not required. Engineering Pay Levels [USD]Engineer II $100, 000 - $130, 000/yearEngineer III (Senior) $120, 000 - $160, 000/yearEngineer IV (Staff) $140, 000 - $190, 000/yearEngineer V (Senior Staff) $170, 000 - $220, 000/yearEngineer VI (Principal Staff) $190, 000 - 250, 000/year BenefitsWe offer stock options and a comprehensive benefits plan. Some of our benefits include health insurance with dental and vision, retirement with an automatic contribution, unlimited paid time off, flexible working hours, sabbatical and company sponsored professional development. ', 'https://www.confiant.com/careers/jobs?gh_jid=5373575004', 2, 16);
