INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (417, 'Senior Data Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-11 15:50:53', 'LISTED', 'About Us: Saint Laurent Consulting is a forward-thinking consultancy that empowers businesses through innovative data solutions. We specialize in harnessing the power of data to drive business success and efficiency. We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced Senior Data Engineer to join our team. Role Overview: As a Senior Data Engineer, you will play a pivotal role in designing, developing, and implementing complex data engineering solutions. You will work with a variety of datasets to support our clients'' data-driven decision-making processes. Your expertise in Databricks and other modern data engineering tools will be crucial in ensuring the scalability, efficiency, and reliability of our data pipelines. Key Responsibilities:Design and develop robust, scalable data pipelines and ETL processes using Databricks, SQL, and cloud-based tools (Azure, AWS).Implement and optimize complex data engineering solutions that handle large volumes of structured and unstructured data.Collaborate with cross-functional teams to gather and understand data requirements, translating them into effective data models and architectures.Ensure data integrity, quality, and security across all data engineering projects.Mentor and guide junior data engineers, sharing best practices and technical knowledge.Continuously evaluate and implement new tools and technologies to enhance data engineering capabilities.Lead the development of data integration solutions with SAP or other enterprise systems, ensuring seamless data flow and consistency. Qualifications:Proven track record of at least 5+ years in data engineering, with extensive experience in Databricks and cloud-based data platforms (Azure, AWS).Databricks certification is highly preferred.Strong expertise in SQL, ETL processes, and data modeling.Experience in implementing complex data engineering solutions for a variety of