INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (424, 'Senior Data Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-10-29 16:21:32', 'LISTED', 'Domain: Retail/ Supply ChainRemote: YesJob Title: Senior Data EngineerCompensation: $75/Hour  With sales of over $100 B, the capability of delivering critical data and building cloud first solutions our teams offer are one of the most critical capabilities of the company. We’re looking for individuals who can bring their core set of knowledge as well as learn new tools to provide new data and capabilities to support the clients ever growing Supply Chain. -Accountable for developing and delivering technological responses to targeted business outcomes. -Analyze, design and develop enterprise data and information architecture deliverables, focusing on data as an asset for Supply Chain and the overall enterprise. -Understand and follow reusable standards, design patterns, guidelines, and configurations to deliver valuable data and information across the enterprise, including direct collaboration with 84.51, where needed. -Demonstrate the company’s core values of respect, honesty, integrity, diversity, inclusion and safety. Key Responsibilities:Create and leverage Databricks notebooks to source, shape and store data using SQL, Python, PySpark-Utilize enterprise standards for data domains and data solutions, focusing on simplified integration and streamlined operational and analytical uses -Ensure there is clarity between ongoing projects, escalating when necessary-Define high-level migration plans to address the gaps between the current and future state -Analyze technology environments to detect critical deficiencies and recommend solutions for improvement -Promote the reuse of data assets, including the management of the data catalog for reference', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4062541194', 297, 1);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (425, 'Data Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-07 20:46:06', 'LISTED', 'Job Details  Job Location  DEN - Greenwood Village, CO  Remote Type  Fully Remote  Position Type  Full Time  Salary Range  $90, 000.00 - $120, 000.00 Salary/year  Description  We are seeking a data engineer to support our data engineering and analytics team. The purpose of this role is to ensure that data products are designed, created, and delivered in a timely manner with high quality.  The ideal candidate for the role of Data Engineer should possess a strongly experienced background in data engineering and related technologies such as SQL scripting and programming, data modeling, Python programming, Snowflake and Databricks data platforms, SQL Server, data lakes, schema change management, and version control.  This role is remote but may require occasional travel to the Corporate office in Denver, CO. The position reports to the Data Manager.  Principal Job Duties:  Develop extract, transform, load (ETL) applications leveraging technologies such as Snowflake, Databricks, Python, DBT, and others. Perform technical research, data profiling, and testing of data assumptions in data sources and in current data products. Creatively provide technical data solutions that will solve business problems and enable analytics teams to build reports and explore data efficiently and quickly. Perform dimensional data modeling and design database objects for ease of access, performance, and consistency. Work with business stakeholders on data and reporting requirements and translate those requirements into technical solutions. Explain data concepts, reports, KPIs, and other technical subjects in business terms. Document development standards, KPI calculations, business glossary terms, table diagrams, and other subjects related to NSA data or reports.   Physical Demands  The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfu