f MLOps and DevOps methodologies, which help improve data processes and streamline the deployment and monitoring of data engineering projects.  Collaboration and Learning: Participate in team meetings, code reviews, and learning opportunities to understand best practices in data engineering. Contribute to collaborative projects, gaining insights into industry standards and innovative techniques.   Required Knowledge, Education, Experience, Skills, And Abilities   Currently pursuing a bachelor’s or master’s degree in computer science, data engineering, software engineering, mathematics, statistics, or a related field.  Basic knowledge of programming languages such as Python, SQL, and Java; familiarity with additional languages like Scala, R, Go, or TypeScript is a plus.  Familiarity with core data engineering concepts such as data pipelines, ETL processes, and data storage solutions.  Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to learn quickly.  Effective written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to collaborate across teams.  High attention to detail and a commitment to maintaining data integrity and quality.', 'https://careers.bartonmalow.com/job/Southfield-Data-Engineer-Intern-MI/1230138500/?utm_source=LINKEDIN&utm_medium=referrer', 309, 113);
