INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (458, 'DevOps Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-10-30 12:22:14', 'LISTED', 'Northwest Partners is looking to hire an experienced Senior DevOps Engineer with at least 7 years of experience to work on a project with one of our premier clients in the technology industry. This contract to hire role offers a dynamic opportunity for a seasoned professional to lead the implementation and management of DevOps practices, primarily leveraging Azure and Google Cloud Platform environments. Applicants must have a strong expertise in Helm, Docker, Kubernetes, Git, Ansible, Dynatrace and Terraform.Applicants must be able to work for any US employer without additional work visa sponsorship. Hybrid position. Needs to be in Dallas office 3 days a week. But will consider remote for the right candidate. What YOU Will Do:DevOps Implementation and Management: Lead the deployment and management of DevOps practices across Azure and GCP, utilizing Kubernetes for orchestration. Implement and maintain Infrastructure as Code (IaC) using Terraform. Monitoring utlizing Dynatrace in a SAAS enviroment. Needs at least 7 years of experienceProject Leadership and Management: Provide guidance and mentorship to project teams (offshore and onshore), ensuring technology projects align with DevOps principles.Process Optimization and Automation: Develop tools and processes to automate tasks and implement continuous integration and deployment pipelines.Continuous Delivery and Deployment: Ensure fast, error-free deployments by optimizing CI/CD practices integrated with Azure and GCP. What YOU Will Bring Us:A four-year college degree in a relevant field plus 7 years of experience, or equivalent.Strong expertise in Azure, GCP, and managing Docker, Kubernetes and Terraform in cloud environments.Proficiency in automation with Terraform and scripting in Python, Bash, or PowerShell.Strong in Ansible and Helm.Proficiency in Git, Experience with cloud monitoring platforms like Dynatrace. Benefits Include:Health Insurance, Vision Insurance, Dental Insurance, Short term Disability, Long-term Disability, Life Insurance, Education Benefits, and more. About Northwest Partners:Northwest Partners is an equal opportunity employer. At Northwest Partners, we are dedicated to moving at the speed of innovation. We work with clients across the globe to provide exceptional knowledge, talent, and resources. As a trusted partner, we merge the client''s vision with our expertise to deliver powerful results. Northwest Partners is known for building and managing elite teams in technology across diverse industries. Our mission is to empower every talent and every client to achieve more.', 'https://northwestpartners.com/careers/?job_id=z5G7h3l6a1kMvyS65NP3c5WHQt48-Oe2rIIWktTSlZM=', 317, 1);
