INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (460, 'Senior Full Stack Developer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-07 14:04:39', 'LISTED', 'Want to learn more about this role and Jobot? Click our Jobot logo and follow our LinkedIn page!  Job details  Remote company is looking for a Full Stack python developer to join their growing software team!  This Jobot Job is hosted by Sydney Weaver  Are you a fit? Easy Apply now by clicking the "Easy Apply" button and sending us your resume.  Salary $90, 000 - $140, 000 per year  A Bit About Us  Join our fast-growing tech company as a Full Stack Engineer with a strong backend focus, where you’ll support our engineering team by alleviating the workload of developers building new features and rearchitecting existing systems. This role involves enhancing our platform through backend improvements and preparing for seamless feature integration, and we’re looking for someone who can bridge frontend and backend development, ideally within U.S. time zones for better collaboration. You’ll work alongside a dedicated team of five developers and four QA specialists, primarily based overseas, helping to balance workloads and drive our platform''s growth. This is an exciting opportunity to make a significant impact on a team focused on developing new features while modernizing our platform.    Why join us?   Great Benefits, 100% Remote Work, Growth Opportunity, Great Culture, PTO, 401K, and much more!  Job Details  Requirements   5+ years of experience in full stack development with a significant focus on backend engineering. Proficiency in Python, Django, and MySQL database management; familiarity with AWS is a strong plus. Experience in modernizing and refactoring legacy systems to support new functionality. Proven ability to troubleshoot and improve conversion rates in complex, high-traffic systems. Frontend experience, preferably with React and basic JavaScript knowledge. Knowledge of current software design best practices, with the ability to implement efficient, scalable code. Ability to work effectively in a team, contributing to deployment processes, rearchitecting projects, and general code maintenance. Based in U.S. time zones for optimal collaboration with global team members.  Interested in hearing more? Easy Apply now by clicking the "Easy Apply" button.  Want to learn more about this role and Jobot?  Click our Jobot logo and follow our LinkedIn page!  ', 'https://jobot.com/apply/senior-full-stack-developer/1375599743?utm_source=LinkedIn', 14, 52);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (461, 'Junior Android Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-04 08:03:15', 'LISTED', 'Who we''re looking for  Have you ever found yourself feverishly working with an Engineering team to solve a complex problem--and found that after what had felt like an hour had only been 10 minutes? If so, we''re looking for hardworking and passionate engineers like yourself to join our team at Fieldwire! Our Android app is built native (95%+ in Kotlin) from the ground up to maximize performance and work in any customer environment online or offline. We believe that native apps should make the most out of their platform and embrace Android at its core, from Material Design to other Android-specific APIs.  The Android team at Fieldwire builds the highest rated construction app on the Play Store. Our engineering teams are multi-functional, co-located with product and design. Fieldwire''s mobile apps are mission critical for the construction teams that use Fieldwire everyday to save time and money on the jobsite.  What you''ll be doing  The primary responsibilities of our next Android Software Engineer will be:  Our Android Engineers are responsible for developing the best possible Android experience for our users. As a member of the Android team, you will work closely with technical and product leadership to develop future features for Android and the Fieldwire platform.  Here is a sample of the kind of challenges you will solve:  Building the fastest mobile plan viewer by displaying 4M pixel images using progressive tilingArchitecting performant list views that need to pull data from 12 different tablesNever losing a single byte of our customer''s data by making sure the app works in every situationDesign, build, and maintain our Android app in KotlinDesigning an advanced 3D model viewer for manipulating complex 3D modelsWork with design and product teams to build high impact featuresKeep up-to-date with the latest and greatest in Android development  At Fieldwire, we''re looking for our next Android Software Engineer to have the following skills and experiences:  Bachelor''s or Master''s degree in CS or equivalent work experience1+ Years of experience working on a production android appExperience writing clean, well-tested, and modular codeStrong understanding of algorithms and data structures  And if you have any of the following, we REALLY want you to apply today!  Experience with reactive programming (RxJava, coroutines)Experience with rendering APIs (eg. OpenGL) or C++ code developmentExperience with advanced debugging tools for memory and performance issues  Why Fieldwire?  Fieldwire is a construction field management software, used on over 1, 000, 000+ projects worldwide. We''re obsessed with improving the way teams work together. We''re building a Field Management Platform dedicated to construction teams — providing operational excellence for one of the world''s largest global industries -- $10 Trillion/year. We''re delivering a superior, easy-to-use product that''s driven by the voice of our customers.  Fieldwire solves the problem of access to information and coordination of labor at a large scale for some of the largest projects in the world. The Fieldwire mobile app has a nearly five-star rating based on thousands of customer reviews. Fieldwire was venture backed by top venture capitalists and has already transformed the way thousands of companies worldwide are working together. Fieldwire was acquired by Hilti for $300M in November 2021.  Compensation:  The estimated pay ranges for this role are as follows: $120, 000- $145, 000  The salary range represents the low and high end of the salary range for this job in the US. Minimums and Maximums may vary based on location. The actual salary offer will carefully consider a wide range of factors such as your skills, qualifications and experience. In addition to the salary you may be eligible for a corporate bonus which can range up to 20%.  Where is the job located?  This role is fully remote within the US. Our office is located right off of Embarcadero Bart station. Easily accessible by all forms of public transportation.  –  Fieldwire is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity, veteran status or any other characteristic protected by law.  ', 'https://grnh.se/802cb7fc2us', 319, 45);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (462, 'Staff Software Engineer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-11 17:46:04', 'LISTED', 'Staff Software Engineer *Paid travel to Miami once a month required*  A heavily backed FinTech start-up, who are building a consumer facing robo-advisory wealth management platform are seeking a Staff Software Engineer to join their growing team! You’d work closely with the CTO on designing and building highly performant, large scale systems with a modern Java stack.  Staff Software Engineer Responsibilities  Own the backend architecture for multiple products – ensuring scalability and performance Drive strategic decisions and have an influence on the product roadmap Act as a hands-on technical leader, building elegant software  Staff Software Engineer Requirements  5+ years of experience designing and building systems with Java (ideally consumer facing products)University degree in CompSci or similar (strong data structure + algorithm knowledge)Experience working in a start-up/scale-up Experience with AWS, Docker and Terraform is nice to have You’d receive significant equity and work with an impressive founding team who have built and sold unicorn businesses before, giving you a unique opportunity to be part of something special.  If you’d like more info, please don’t hesitate to apply!', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4070038070', 320, 1);
