INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (473, 'Data Engineer', false, '', '2024-10-31 22:58:54', 'LISTED', 'The Select Group is looking for a strong Data Engineer for one of their top tech clients. This is going to be a long term contract located in Cupertino, CO (Hybrid – 3 days onsite, 2 days remote). As a Data Engineer for the Growth Marketing Operations team, you will design, develop, and work on data solutions to support Growth initiatives for the organizations’ Media Products and Services. This role will help scale our data signals program and closely partner with engineering teams across the organization. You will work across several lines of business and stakeholder teams to help optimize the delivery of data signals, data validation, and documentation. The Data Signals Engineer will leverage data assets to enable our marketers to make decisions that reach the right users at the right time.  Data Engineer Requirements  High proficiency in SQL (Snowflake, Teradata, any other DB).Data Engineering solutions experience - designing and researching technical solutions for new data pipelinesGood understanding of database modeling, ETL and data warehousing principlesHigh proficiency in Python scripting and RestAPIs.Data Marketing experienceAbility to analyze current architecture and develop steps and processes to improve upon itExperience converting business needs into functional designExcellent debugging and documentation experience, particularly with iOS appsExcellent communication skills; experience working with cross functional teams, discussing technical design, back-end architecture, and data pipelines.  Plus Skills  Experience working with privacy and compliance engineering teams, to ensure data and systems are in complianceExperience in Tableau or similar Data Visualization toolsExperience developing and delivering multi-mode communications that convey a clear understanding of the unique needs of different audiencesAbility to prioritize and succeed under rapidly changing, time-constrained schedulesCurious mindset with an ability to condense complex concepts into clear and concise action itemsExperience in working in a global organization  Data Engineer Responsibilities  Building Data Systems: Design and develop new data systems or improve existing ones. These systems (or "data signals") help marketers understand user behaviors and optimize their marketing efforts.SQL and Python scriptingResearch and design of systemsSolutions documentationValidationCollaborating Across Teams: Partner closely with various teams (like engineering and compliance) to ensure data is high-quality, properly documented, and aligns with privacy standards.Analyzing and Improving: Regularly check current data architecture and find ways to make it better, like more efficient data processing or stronger privacy measures. TSG is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, or status as a protected veteran.  70761  ', 'https://www.selectgroup.com/career-seekers/careers/job/70761-data-engineer-cupertino-ca/?utm_source=LinkedIn', 204, 122);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (474, 'Sr. Python Developer', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-04 14:04:58', 'LISTED', 'ABOUT THE COMPANY:  Nymbus (https://nymbus.com/) isn''t just a leader in fintech; we''re a community of innovators passionate about reimagining banking. Our award-winning modern core platform and cloud-based technology serve as the backbone for financial institutions eager to modernize and excel.  Here, you won''t just be part of a tech revolution; you''ll be at the helm, driving change. You''ll fit right in if you''re a creative thinker eager to lessen technical debt and elevate agility for banks and credit unions. Our culture thrives on collaboration, integrity, and a client-first approach.  Your journey with us won''t simply advance your career; it will offer the chance to shape an industry alongside like-minded professionals. We''re excited to consider you a key player in this transformative chapter. Thank you for contemplating a role with Nymbus.  POSITION SUMMARY:  Nymbus is looking for an experienced Full-Stack Developer to join our agile squad and develop the front and backend of our enterprise applications as well as integrations. The position of Full-Stack Developer combines technical experience, analytical abilities, and sound coding skills.  ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS/RESPONSIBILITIES:  Expertise in Python/Javascript: The candidate must be capable of learning and maintaining existing system components developed in Jython and Javascript, with the objective of modernizing and improving these components over time.    Product development: Candidate must be able to work closely with distributed team members to deliver well thought out, configurable, high quality, scalable solutions used across our bank and credit union clients.      Strong understanding of database schemas, data modeling, and database design principles: Candidates must demonstrate expertise in relational (and optionally non-relational) database concepts to programmatically maintain data layer consistency between environments.Proficiency in SQL and Database Scripting: Strong skills in writing and optimizing SQL queries and scripts are essential.Knowledge of Source Control Management (SCM) systems: Candidates should be familiar with SCM tools like Git, SVN, or Mercurial, particularly in the context of managing database schema versions.    Experience with Continuous Integration/Continuous Deployment (CI/CD) pipelines: A solid understanding of CI/CD principles and tools (e.g., Jenkins, GitLab CI, CircleCI) in relation to database deployments is required.      Familiarity with ORM tools: Knowledge of Object-Relational Mapping tools (e.g., Hibernate, Entity Framework, Sequelize) is advantageous but not essential  QUALIFICATIONS:  Programing Experience: Minimum 5 years in a Python & Javascript development role. Proven understanding of web technologies, such as Jython, JavaScript, SCSS, HTML5, XML, and/or Ajax. Experience in Programmatic Management of Databases: Minimum of 2-4 years of experience in database management and architecture. Candidates should have knowledge of database design, database query languages, and automated management of the data layer. Remote Work: Strong communication skills in English (spoken and written)Positive attitude, willing to learn, build relationships, solve problems and contributeAble to maintain a strong work ethic in a rapidly changing and fast-paced environmentExperience and preference for working 100% remote with a distributed team. TERMINOLOGY & FRAMEWORKS:  Data ModelingSQLGitGitLab CIJython/GraalVM programming and system maintenanceJavascript, HTML, SCSSAPIs  SALARY & BENEFITS:  $135, 000 - $150, 000 Annual Salary Annual Cash Bonus and Equity Options commensurate with the role level and experience100% Fully RemoteRobust 401(k) plan with company matchInsurance - Health, Dental and Vision (Nymbus covers 100% of the Healthcare and Basic Dental premiums)Flexible Paid Time Off  Ready to join? We invite you to watch this video and learn who we are and how we build and innovates together!  Let''s Go!', 'https://grnh.se/31579d6b4us', 178, 40);
