INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (478, 'Full-Stack Developer (Consultant)', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-06 02:51:51', 'LISTED', 'About Us  Way to Win was founded in 2017 as a space for donors and organizers alike to come together and create strategies that build progressive power by cultivating both electoral wins and progressive governance to follow. Our work starts at the local level and builds up to national reform. We are led by the movement leaders working in communities closest to the injustice of the current political norms. We aim for bold ideas to create a tangibly better future that works for the most marginalized of people.  Way to Win works in relationships with multiple organizations to accomplish its mission, including PACs.  Way to Win is seeking a values-aligned, full-stack developer with knowledge in WordPress, MySQL, Salesforce, Mailchimp and more, who is committed to racial and economic justice and democratic participation.  While we are currently hiring a contractor to build out a membership portal of our main website, we are seeking a long-term partner that can work effectively with our team. As a long-term partner, we would reach out to you for website updates, maintenance, and more. This role will work closely with the Director of Design and Design Coordinator, and be responsible for developing our creative ideas into seamless, secure, high-performing websites and website integrations—bringing our vision and strategy to life.  As a virtual office with team members spread out from NYC to Hawaiʻi, we require a highly motivated go-getter, able to effectively self-manage and lean into our agile and fast-paced culture. We are looking for a contractor who is able to dedicate their time to complete projects with speed, attention to detail, thoroughness, and collaboration.  Deliverables  Build Out  Creation of 6 pages as a subdomain to main website:   Member Login Page: Multiple ways for user to sign-in  Dashboard Homepage: Widget page  Calendar Page: Filter/sort/search functions, register, attachments, add to calendar  Resources Page: Embed documents, filter/sort/search function  Library: Filter/sort/search functions, RSS feed for news articles, Mailchimp integration, and potentially social media integration  Member Directory: Salesforce integration, filter/sort/search function, interactive maps and graphs based on member data    Security    Implement strong user authentication: This needs to be a secure member platform in which users can login via username and password, Gmail, Ymail, Facebook, Instagram, X, etc. Two-Factor authentication included.  User Access: Members should only have access to view the site, with the exception of being able to edit their own personal information in the member directory portion.    Integrations    Calendar Events: Integrate a calendar system to house upcoming events, sign ups, filters/sorts, pre- and post- call documentation.  DocSend: Embed secure documents that live in our Doscsend account, which removes a step for the user to click into another site for the information they are looking for.  Mailchimp: Potential integration to bring in previous emails that were sent out.  Salesforce CRM: Integrate a plugin to help synchronize member data between the Wordpress site and Salesforce. When a change is made in Salesforce, it should automatically be applied to Wordpress. But, if a change is made in Wordpress it should notify our team to accept the changes, which would be reflected on both platforms.    Maintenance    Quarterly maintenance of the website (front/back end systems).   Qualifications & Requirements   Proficient in front- and back-end development, with specific knowledge of WordPress, CMS development, MySQL, PHP, HTML5, JS/JQuery, CSS, Salesforce, and possibly Mailchimp integrations.  Ability to think outside the box to utilize various programming techniques to achieve desired results with optimal performance on both desktop and mobile devices.  Create a user friendly site (on both the front and back end), one that is easily accessible and maintainable for our team.  Extreme attention to detail and ability to work collaboratively. This project will require effective communication and coordination with the Design Team. *Qualified candidates should be able to meet with the Design team over Zoom to review status and receive feedback.    Rate  $45.00 per hour on 1099 Status.  You can learn more about Way to Win here .', 'https://workforcenow.adp.com/mascsr/default/mdf/recruitment/recruitment.html?jobId=564733&ccId=19000101_000001&source=LI&type=JS&lang=en_US&selectedMenuKey=CurrentOpenings&cid=488c3bcb-f5e6-4d18-86f3-a476dacbfe8f', 327, 1);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (479, 'Data Engineer – Big Data & AWS - JOBID465', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-11 13:59:04', 'LISTED', 'Job Summary:We are seeking a highly skilled Big Data Engineer to join our data engineering team. The ideal candidate will be proficient in Python programming, experienced in big data technologies, and well-versed in data manipulation libraries such as Pandas, Polars, and NumPy. This role requires strong experience in designing, building, and orchestrating data pipelines, as well as expertise in developing distributed computing applications using PySpark. If you are passionate about big data, have hands-on experience with AWS services, and thrive in a collaborative environment, we would love to hear from you. Key Responsibilities:Design, develop, and maintain large-scale data pipelines and ETL processes for data ingestion, transformation, and processing.Implement distributed computing applications with Spark and PySpark for high-performance data processing.Utilize libraries like Pandas, Polars, and NumPy for data manipulation and analysis.Develop and orchestrate data pipelines on cloud environments, primarily using AWS services (EMR, Lambda, Glue ETL, S3, and more).Write, maintain, and execute automated unit tests following Test-Driven Development (TDD) practices.Design and build APIs to support data access and integration.Create and maintain data visualizations using Tableau for analytical insights.Manage both relational and NoSQL databases (RDS PostgreSQL, DynamoDB, Timeseries databases) and design data models (normalization, denormalization, schema design).Implement serverless architectures leveraging AWS services like Lambda, S3, ECS, Kinesis, and VPC.Ensure data quality and troubleshoot data issues with strong analytical skills.Collaborate with cross-functional teams to enhance data solutions and ensure best practices in code quality and version control.Work with CI/CD pipelines and participate in peer code reviews. Required Skills & Qualifications:Programming Languages: Proficiency in Python for data engineering and automation.Big Data & Distributed Computing: Advanced expertise in Spark, PySpark, SQL, Presto, and HIVE.Data Manipulation: Experience with libraries like Pandas, Polars, and NumPy.Cloud Services (AWS): Extensive experience with AWS services, including EMR, Lambda, Glue ETL, Step Functions, S3, ECS, Kinesis, IAM, RDS, DynamoDB, Athena, SNS, SQS, VPC, and others.Data Warehousing: Knowledge of Amazon Redshift and other data warehousing concepts.Data Modeling: Skills in designing and implementing data models for normalized and denormalized structures.Visualization Tools: Proficiency in Tableau for data visualization and reporting.APIs: Experience in building and managing APIs for data integration.Software Development Practices: Strong understanding of source control, unit testing, TDD, and CI/CD processes.Analytical Skills: Ability to troubleshoot and resolve data issues effectively.Domain Knowledge: Understanding of trading and investment data, and experience with OneTick or KDB is a plus. Preferred Qualifications:Familiarity with Timeseries databases and data streaming frameworks.Experience in serverless architecture design on AWS.Knowledge of data warehousing and ETL best practices.Prior experience in financial or trading environments is a bonus.', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4072006245', 328, 1);
INSERT INTO public."Jobs" VALUES (480, 'REMOTE Sr. Full-Stack Engineer - React, Node, Express', true, 'Remote', '2024-11-02 01:49:10', 'LISTED', 'Job Title: Sr. Full-Stack Software Engineer  Location: 100% REMOTE!  Salary: $150-180k/year  Requirements: NodeJS, Express, Typescript, any frontend framework, Postgres  We are a fully-funded startup backed by the same people behind Uber, Refinery29, Mint, Warby Parker, Hotel Tonight & Looker! We''ve built a financially and tehnically savvy product that our customers love. We''re fully-funded, which proves that no matter what the market holds, our investors believe in us! We''re quickly expanding.. We''ve hired 150+ people in the past 12 months and we''re not done yet!  We''re looking for self-starters who enjoy tackling challenges and working with others to find solutions. This is a dynamic environment, offering a fantastic opportunity for someone eager to join a growing tech team at a mid-stage start-up and directly contribute to developing and improving our products.  Our stack: Node.js with Typescript, React.js front-end, and PostgreSQL.  What You''ll Be Doing  Engage in practical software development, utilizing your skills, knowledge, and past experiences.Design and execute technical solutions.Develop and enhance team processes and best practices based on project insights.Provide mentorship and technical guidance to less experienced engineers on the team.  What We''re Looking For  5+ years of Software Development experience3+ years of recent Node.JS & Express.JS experience (Express.JS experience MUST be OG Vanilla, not Nest.js)Frontend experience in any modern Javascript framework (React, Angular, Vue, Svelte, etc.)PostgreSQLTypescriptBS in Computer Science, Mathematics, Chemistry, or similar  Benefits  Salary - $150, 000 - $180, 000EQUITY!Medical, dental & vision insurance for both employees and dependentsWellness and mental health benefitsFlexible PTOHome office setup401kInternet/phone expenses covered and MORE!   E