s of professional software development or data engineering experience Expertise in computer, data, and analytics engineering. Expertise in SQL and its use in code-based ETL frameworks preferably dbt with a focus on reuse and efficiency. Expertise in ETL/ELT pipelines, analytical data modeling, aggregations, and metrics Expertise of analytical modeling architectures, including the Kimball design Strong communication skills in writing and conversation, including writing engineering training documentation. Preferred Requirements Fluency in a development language such as Python Familiarity with metadata management tools such as Atlan Experience building dashboards, reports, and models in business intelligence tools such as Tableau or Looker Expertise with tools we use every day: Storage: Snowflake, AWS Storage Services (S3, RDS, Glacier, DynamoDB) and Postgres ETL/ELT: Airflow, dbt, Matillion, Fivetran BI: Looker, Tableau Experience with tools we don’t use, but should Proven passion and talent for teaching fellow engineers and non-engineers Proven passion for building and learning: open source contributions, pet projects, self-education, Stack Overflow Proven technical leadership in project delivery. Experience in education or ed-tec', 'https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/4074798144', 3, 1);
